msgid "Integrating an Antivirus"
msgstr "Tích hợp một trình diệt vi-rút"

msgid "<primary>antivirus</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>antivirus</primary>"

msgid "The many viruses circulating as attachments to emails make it important to set up an antivirus at the entry point of the company network, since despite an awareness campaign, some users will still open attachments from obviously shady messages."
msgstr "Rất nhiều vi-rút di chuyển dưới dạng tài liệu đính kèm trong những thư điện tử khiến cho việc cài đặt một trình diệt vi-rút ở cổng vào của mạng công ty rất quan trọng, bởi dù có một chiến dịch tăng cường sự hiểu biết, một số người sử dụng sẽ vẫn mở các tài liệu đính kèm từ những thông điệp này dù thoạt nhìn rất đáng nghi."

msgid "The Falcot administrators selected <command>clamav</command> for their free antivirus. The main package is <emphasis role=\"pkg\">clamav</emphasis>, but they also installed a few extra packages such as <emphasis role=\"pkg\">arj</emphasis>, <emphasis role=\"pkg\">unzoo</emphasis>, <emphasis role=\"pkg\">unrar</emphasis> and <emphasis role=\"pkg\">lha</emphasis>, since they are required for the antivirus to analyze attachments archived in one of these formats."
msgstr "Các nhà quản trị hệ thống Falcot đã lựa chọn <command>clamav</command> làm trình duyệt vi-rút miễn phí của họ. Gói phần mềm chủ lực là <emphasis role=\"pkg\">clamav</emphasis>, nhưng họ cũng đã cài một vài gói phần mềm thêm như <emphasis role=\"pkg\">arj</emphasis>, <emphasis role=\"pkg\">unzoo</emphasis>, <emphasis role=\"pkg\">unrar</emphasis> và <emphasis role=\"pkg\">lha</emphasis>, bởi chúng được cần tới bởi trình duyệt vi-rút để rà soát các tài liệu đính kèm lưu dưới một trong các định dạng này."

msgid "<primary><command>clamav</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>clamav</command></primary>"

msgid "<primary><command>clamav-milter</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>clamav-milter</command></primary>"

msgid "The task of interfacing between antivirus and the email server goes to <command>clamav-milter</command>. A <emphasis>milter</emphasis> (short for <emphasis>mail filter</emphasis>) is a filtering program specially designed to interface with email servers. A milter uses a standard application programming interface (API) that provides much better performance than filters external to the email servers. Milters were initially introduced by <emphasis>Sendmail</emphasis>, but <emphasis>Postfix</emphasis> soon followed suit."
msgstr "Công việc kết nối trình diệt vi-rút và máy phục vụ thư điện tử thuộc về <command>clamav-milter</command>. Một <emphasis>milter</emphasis> (viết tắt của <emphasis>mail filter(bộ lọc thư)</emphasis>) là một chương trình lọc được thiết kế riêng để giao tiếp với các máy phục vụ thư điện tử. Một milter(bộ lọc thư) sử dụng một chuẩn kết nối lập trình ứng dụng(API) vốn cung cấp hiệu suất cao hơn các bộ lọc nằm bên ngoài các máy phục vụ thư điện tử. Các bộ lọc thư này đầu tiên được giới thiệu bởi <emphasis>Sendmail</emphasis>, nhưng <emphasis>Postfix</emphasis> sớm đuổi theo xu hướng."

msgid "<emphasis>QUICK LOOK</emphasis> A milter for Spamassassin"
msgstr "<emphasis>SƠ LƯỢC</emphasis> Một bộ lọc thư(milter) cho Spamassasin"

msgid "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">spamass-milter</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">spamass-milter</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "The <emphasis role=\"pkg\">spamass-milter</emphasis> package provides a milter based on <emphasis>SpamAssassin</emphasis>, the famous unsolicited email detector. It can be used to flag messages as probable spams (by adding an extra header) and/or to reject the messages altogether if their “spamminess” score goes beyond a given threshold."
msgstr "Gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">spamass-milter</emphasis> cung cấp một bộ lọc thư dựa trên <emphasis>SpamAssassin</emphasis>, một chương trình nổi tiếng phát hiện thư điện tử được gửi không ai yêu cầu. Nó có thể được sử dụng để đánh dấu các thông điệp có thể là thư rác (bằng cách thêm một tiêu đề thêm) và/hoặc từ chối hết những thư điện tử nếu điểm “thư rác“ của chúng vượt qua một mức điểm cho trước."

msgid "Once the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">clamav-milter</emphasis> package is installed, the milter should be reconfigured to run on a TCP port rather than on the default named socket. This can be achieved with <command>dpkg-reconfigure clamav-milter</command>. When prompted for the “Communication interface with Sendmail”, answer “<literal>inet:10002@127.0.0.1</literal>”."
msgstr "Khi gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">clamav-milter</emphasis> được cài đặt, bộ lọc thư đó nên được cấu hình lại để chạy trên cổng TCP hơn là trên một socket chuẩn. Điều này có thể đạt được bằng <command>dpkg-reconfigure clamav-milter</command>. Khi được hỏi về “Cách kết nối giao tiếp với Sendmail (Communication interface with Sendmail)”, trả lời “<literal>inet:10002@127.0.0.1</literal>”."

msgid "<emphasis>NOTE</emphasis> Real TCP port vs named socket"
msgstr "<emphasis>GHI CHÚ</emphasis> Cổng TCP thật và socket có tên"

msgid "The reason why we use a real TCP port rather than the named socket is that the postfix daemons often run chrooted and do not have access to the directory hosting the named socket. You could also decide to keep using a named socket and pick a location within the chroot (<filename>/var/spool/postfix/</filename>)."
msgstr "Lý do chúng tôi sử dụng cổng TCP thật thì vì một socket có tên là vì các tiến trình nền postfix thường chạy với thư mục gốc được đổi và không có truy cập tới thư mục chứa socket có tên. Bạn có thể quyết sử dụng một socket có tên và chọn một vị trí trong môi trường đã thay đổi thư mục gốc (<filename>/var/spool/postfix/</filename>)."

msgid "The standard ClamAV configuration fits most situations, but some important parameters can still be customized with <command>dpkg-reconfigure clamav-base</command>."
msgstr "Cấu hình ClamAV chuẩn phù hợp cho đa số các trường hợp, nhưng một số tham số quan trọng có thể được tùy chỉnh với lệnh <command>dpkg-reconfigure clamav-base</command>."

msgid "The last step involves telling Postfix to use the recently-configured filter. This is a simple matter of adding the following directive to <filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename>:"
msgstr "Bước cuối cùng liên quan tới việc bảo Postfix sử dụng bộ lọc được cấu hình gần đây nhất. Đây đơn giản được thực hiện bằng cách thêm chỉ thị sau vào tập tin <filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename>:"

msgid ""
"\n"
"# Virus check with clamav-milter\n"
"smtpd_milters = inet:[127.0.0.1]:10002"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"# Virus check with clamav-milter\n"
"smtpd_milters = inet:[127.0.0.1]:10002"

msgid "If the antivirus causes problems, this line can be commented out, and <command>service postfix reload</command> should be run so that this change is taken into account."
msgstr "Nếu chương trình diệt vi-rút gây ra vấn đề, dòng sau có thể được chuyển thành ghi chú, và lệnh <command>service postfix reload</command> nên được chạy để thay đổi này được áp dụng."

msgid "<emphasis>IN PRACTICE</emphasis> Testing the antivirus"
msgstr "<emphasis>TRÊN THỰC TẾ</emphasis> Kiểm tra chương trình diệt vi-rút"

msgid "Once the antivirus is set up, its correct behavior should be tested. The simplest way to do that is to send a test email with an attachment containing the <filename>eicar.com</filename> (or <filename>eicar.com.zip</filename>) file, which can be downloaded online: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://www.eicar.org/86-0-Intended-use.html\" />"
msgstr "Một khi trình diệt vi-rút được cài đặt, hành vi đúng của nó nên được thử nghiệm. Cách đơn giản nhất để làm điều đó là gửi một thư điện tử kiểm tra với một tài liệu đính kèm chứa tập tin <filename>eicar.com</filename> (hay <filename>eicar.com.zip</filename>) vốn có thể được tải về từ mạng: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://www.eicar.org/86-0-Intended-use.html\" />"

msgid "This file is not a true virus, but a test file that all antivirus software on the market diagnose as a virus to allow checking installations."
msgstr "Tập tin này không phải là một vi-rút thật sự, nhưng là một tập tin thử nghiệm mà tất cả chương trình diệt vi-rút trên thị trường chẩn đoán là một vi-rút để cho phép kiểm tra các bản cài đặt chương trình diệt vi-rút."

msgid "All messages handled by Postfix now go through the antivirus filter."
msgstr "Tất cả các thông điệp được xử lý bởi Postfix sẽ đi qua bộ lọc diệt vi-rút."

msgid "Authenticated SMTP"
msgstr "SMTP có chứng thực"

msgid "Being able to send emails requires an SMTP server to be reachable; it also requires said SMTP server to send emails through it. For roaming users, this may need regularly changing the configuration of the SMTP client, since Falcot's SMTP server rejects messages coming from IP addresses apparently not belonging to the company. Two solutions exist: either the roaming user installs an SMTP server on their computer, or they still use the company server with some means of authenticating as an employee. The former solution is not recommended since the computer won't be permanently connected, and it won't be able to retry sending messages in case of problems; we will focus on the latter solution."
msgstr "Việc có thể gửi thư điện tử buộc phải kết nối được tới máy phục vụ SMTP; nó cũng cần một máy phục vụ SMTP như vậy để gửi thư điện tử xuyên qua nó. Đối với những người sử dụng hay chuyển vùng, điều này cần phải thay đổi thường xuyên cấu hình của chương trình khách SMTP(SMTP client), bởi máy phục vụ SMTP của Falcot từ chối những thông điệp đến từ những địa chỉ IP rõ ràng không thuộc về công ty. Có hai giải pháp: hoặc người sử dụng chuyển vùng cài đặt một máy phục vụ SMTP trên máy của họ, hoặc họ vẫn sử dụng máy phục vụ của công ty với một cách nào đó để đăng nhập như một nhân viên công ty. Giải pháp đầu điên không được khuyến cáo bởi máy tính của họ không được kết nối liên tục, và nó sẽ không thể thử lại việc gửi các thông điệp trong trường hợp sự cố; chúng ta sẽ tập trung vào giải pháp tiếp theo."

msgid "SMTP authentication in Postfix relies on SASL (<emphasis>Simple Authentication and Security Layer</emphasis>). It requires installing the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libsasl2-modules</emphasis> and <emphasis role=\"pkg\">sasl2-bin</emphasis> packages, then registering a password in the SASL database for each user that needs authenticating on the SMTP server. This is done with the <command>saslpasswd2</command> command, which takes several parameters. The <literal>-u</literal> option defines the authentication domain, which must match the <literal>smtpd_sasl_local_domain</literal> parameter in the Postfix configuration. The <literal>-c</literal> option allows creating a user, and <literal>-f</literal> allows specifying the file to use if the SASL database needs to be stored at a different location than the default (<filename>/etc/sasldb2</filename>)."
msgstr "Chứng thực SMTP trong Postfix dựa trên SASL ("<emphasis>Lớp Chứng thực và An ninh - Simple Authentication and Security Layer</emphasis>). Nó đòi hỏi việc cài đặt các gói <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libsasl2-modules</emphasis> và <emphasis role=\"pkg\">sasl2-bin</emphasis>, sau đó phải đăng ký một mật mã trên cơ sở dữ liệu SASL cho mỗi người sử dụng cần đăng nhập trên máy phục vụ SMTP. Điều này được thực hiện bằng lệnh <command>saslpasswd2</command>, vốn cần một vài tham số. Lựa chọn <literal>-u</literal> định nghĩa một miền đăng nhập (authentication domain), vốn phải hợp với tham biến <literal>smtpd_sasl_local_domain</literal> của cấu hình Postfix. Lựa chọn <literal>-c</literal> cho phép tạo một người dùng, và <literal>-f</literal> cho phép chỉ định một tập tin để sử dụng nếu cơ sở dữ liệu SASL cần được lưu ở một địa chỉ không phải là địa chỉ ngầm định (<filename>/etc/sasldb2</filename>)."

msgid ""
"\n"
"<computeroutput># </computeroutput><userinput>saslpasswd2 -u `postconf -h myhostname` -f /var/spool/postfix/etc/sasldb2 -c jean</userinput>\n"
"<computeroutput>[... type jean's password twice ...]</computeroutput>"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<computeroutput># </computeroutput><userinput>saslpasswd2 -u `postconf -h myhostname` -f /var/spool/postfix/etc/sasldb2 -c jean</userinput>\n"
"<computeroutput>[... type jean's password twice ...]</computeroutput>"

msgid "Note that the SASL database was created in Postfix's directory. In order to ensure consistency, we also turn <filename>/etc/sasldb2</filename> into a symbolic link pointing at the database used by Postfix, with the <command>ln -sf /var/spool/postfix/etc/sasldb2 /etc/sasldb2</command> command."
msgstr "Ghi chú một điều rằng cơ sở dữ liệu SASL được tạo ra trước đó trong thư mục của Postfix. Để đảm bảo sự thống nhất, chúng ta cũng chuyển <filename>/etc/sasldb2</filename>  thành một đường link tượng trưng (symbolic link) dẫn đến cơ sở dữ liệu sử dụng bởi Postfix, bằng lệnh <command>ln -sf /var/spool/postfix/etc/sasldb2 /etc/sasldb2</command>"

msgid "Now we need to configure Postfix to use SASL. First the <literal>postfix</literal> user needs to be added to the <literal>sasl</literal> group, so that it can access the SASL account database. A few new parameters are also needed to enable SASL, and the <literal>smtpd_recipient_restrictions</literal> parameter needs to be configured to allow SASL-authenticated clients to send emails freely."
msgstr "Bây giờ chúng ta cần cấu hình Postfix để sử dụng SASL. Trước tiên, người dùng <literal>postfix</literal> cần được thêm vào nhóm <literal>sasl</literal>, để người dùng này có thể truy cập cơ sở dữ liệu tài khoản SASL. Một vài tham số mới cũng cần để kích hoạt SASL, và tham biến <literal>smtpd_recipient_restrictions</literal> cần phải được cấu hình để cho phép các vị khách đã được chứng thực thông qua SASL gửi thư điện tử một cách thoải mái."

msgid "Enabling SASL in <filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename>"
msgstr "Kích hoạt SASL trong <filename>/etc/postfix/main.cf</filename>""

msgid ""
"\n"
"# Enable SASL authentication\n"
"smtpd_sasl_auth_enable = yes\n"
"# Define the SASL authentication domain to use\n"
"smtpd_sasl_local_domain = $myhostname\n"
"[...]\n"
"# Adding permit_sasl_authenticated before reject_unauth_destination\n"
"# allows relaying mail sent by SASL-authenticated users\n"
"smtpd_recipient_restrictions = permit_mynetworks,\n"
"    permit_sasl_authenticated,\n"
"    reject_unauth_destination,\n"
"[...]"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"# Kích hoạt chứng thực SASL\n"
"smtpd_sasl_auth_enable = yes\n"
"# Xác định miền chứng thực SASL để sử dụng (SASL authentication domain)\n"
"smtpd_sasl_local_domain = $myhostname\n"
"[...]\n"
"# Thêm permit_sasl_authenticated vào trước reject_unauth_destination\n"
"# cho phép chuyển phát thư gửi bởi những người dùng đã được chứng thực qua SASL\n"
"smtpd_recipient_restrictions = permit_mynetworks,\n"
"    permit_sasl_authenticated,\n"
"    reject_unauth_destination,\n"
"[...]"

msgid "<emphasis>EXTRA</emphasis> Authenticated SMTP client"
msgstr "<emphasis>THÔNG TIN THÊM</emphasis> Chương trình khách SMTP đã được chứng thực"

msgid "Most email clients are able to authenticate to an SMTP server before sending outgoing messages, and using that feature is a simple matter of configuring the appropriate parameters. If the client in use does not provide that feature, the workaround is to use a local Postfix server and configure it to relay email via the remote SMTP server. In this case, the local Postfix itself will be the client that authenticates with SASL. Here are the required parameters:"
msgstr "Đa số những chương trình khách thư điện tử có thể chứng thực với một máy phục vụ SMTP trước khi gửi các thông điệp ra ngoài, và sử dụng tính năng này đơn giản chỉ cần cấu hình những tham số phù hợp. Nếu chương trình khách đang được sử dụng đó không cung cấp tính năng đó, cách khác là sử dụng một máy phục vụ Postfix nội bộ và cấu hình nó để chuyển phát thư điện tử thông qua máy phục vụ SMTP. Trong trường hợp này, chính máy Postfix nội bộ sẽ là chương trình khách chứng thực thông qua SASL. Sau đây là những thông số bắt buộc:"

msgid ""
"\n"
"smtp_sasl_auth_enable = yes\n"
"smtp_sasl_password_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/sasl_passwd\n"
"relay_host = [mail.falcot.com]"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"smtp_sasl_auth_enable = yes\n"
"smtp_sasl_password_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/sasl_passwd\n"
"relay_host = [mail.falcot.com]"

msgid "The <filename>/etc/postfix/sasl_passwd</filename> file needs to contain the username and password to use for authenticating on the <literal>mail.falcot.com</literal> server. Here is an example:"
msgstr "Tập tin <filename>/etc/postfix/sasl_passwd</filename> cần phải chứa một tên tài khoản và mật mã để sử dụng tính năng chứng thực trên máy phục vụ <literal>mail.falcot.com</literal>. Sau đây là một ví dụ:"

msgid ""
"\n"
"[mail.falcot.com]   joe:LyinIsji"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"[mail.falcot.com]   joe:LyinIsji"

msgid "As for all Postfix maps, this file must be turned into <filename>/etc/postfix/sasl_passwd.db</filename> with the <command>postmap</command> command."
msgstr "Giống như tất cả các ánh xạ Postfix(Postfix maps), tập tin này phải được chuyển thành <filename>/etc/postfix/sasl_passwd.db</filename> với lệnh <command>postmap</command>."

msgid "Web Server (HTTP)"
msgstr "Máy phục vụ Web (HTTP)"

msgid "The Falcot Corp administrators decided to use the Apache HTTP server, included in Debian <emphasis role=\"distribution\">Jessie</emphasis> at version 2.4.10."
msgstr "Những nhà quản trị của công ty Falcot quyết định sử dụng máy phục vụ HTTP Apache, có sẵn trong Debian <emphasis role=\"distribution\">Jessie</emphasis> tại phiên bản 2.4.10."

msgid "<primary><command>apache</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>apache</command></primary>"

msgid "<primary>server</primary><secondary>web</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>máy phục vụ</primary><secondary>web</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>web server</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>máy phục vụ web</primary>"

msgid "<primary>server</primary><secondary>HTTP</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>máy phục vụ</primary><secondary>HTTP</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>HTTP</primary><secondary>server</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>HTTP</primary><secondary>máy phục vụ</secondary>"

msgid "<emphasis>ALTERNATIVE</emphasis> Other web servers"
msgstr "<emphasis>LỰA CHỌN THAY THẾ</emphasis> Những máy phục vụ web khác"

msgid "Apache is merely the most widely-known (and widely-used) web server, but there are others; they can offer better performance under certain workloads, but this has its counterpart in the smaller number of available features and modules. However, when the prospective web server is built to serve static files or to act as a proxy, the alternatives, such as <emphasis role=\"pkg\">nginx</emphasis> and <emphasis role=\"pkg\">lighttpd</emphasis>, are worth investigating."
msgstr "Apache chỉ là một máy phục vụ web được biết đến khá nhiều (và được sử dụng rộng rãi), nhưng có những nhà cung cấp khác; họ có thể cung cấp hiệu suất cao dưới một lượng tải nhất định nào đó, nhưng lựa chọn này bị cân bằng lại bởi ít tính năng và mô-đun hơn. Tuy nhiên, khi máy phục vụ web sẽ được lựa chọn để cung cấp các tập tin tĩnh hay để hoạt động như một trạm chuyển hướng, những lựa chọn khác, như là <emphasis role=\"pkg\">nginx</emphasis> và <emphasis role=\"pkg\">lighttpd</emphasis>, rất đáng để xem xét."

msgid "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">nginx</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">nginx</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">lighttpd</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">lighttpd</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "Installing Apache"
msgstr "Cài đặt Apache"

msgid "Installing the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">apache2</emphasis> package is all that is needed. It contains all the modules, including the <emphasis>Multi-Processing Modules</emphasis> (MPMs) that affect how Apache handles parallel processing of many requests (those used to be provided in separate <emphasis role=\"pkg\">apache2-mpm-*</emphasis> packages). It will also pull <emphasis role=\"pkg\">apache2-utils</emphasis> containing the command line utilities that we will discover later."
msgstr "Cài đặt gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">apache2</emphasis> là tất cả những gì cần thiết. Nó chứa tất cả các mô-đun, bao gồm <emphasis>Những Mô-đun đa xử lý(Multi-Processing Modules)</emphasis> (MPMs) kiểm soát việc Apache thực hiện việc xử lý song song những yêu cầu (những mô-đun trước đây được cung cấp dưới hình thức các gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">apache2-mpm-*</emphasis> rời rạc). Nó sẽ kéo về gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">apache2-utils</emphasis> vốn chứa những tiện ích dòng lệnh mà chúng ta sẽ khám phá sau."

msgid "The MPM in use affects significantly the way Apache will handle concurrent requests. With the <emphasis>worker</emphasis> MPM, it uses <emphasis>threads</emphasis> (lightweight processes), whereas with the <emphasis>prefork</emphasis> MPM it uses a pool of processes created in advance. With the <emphasis>event</emphasis> MPM it also uses threads, but the inactive connections (notably those kept open by the HTTP <emphasis>keep-alive</emphasis> feature) are handed back to a dedicated management thread."
msgstr "MPM khi đang hoạt động ảnh hưởng lớn đến cách Apache xử lý các yêu cầu cùng lúc. Với MPM <emphasis>worker</emphasis>, nó sử dụng các <emphasis>thread</emphasis> (các tiến trình nhỏ và nhẹ), trong khi MPM <emphasis>prefork</emphasis> sử dụng một kho tiến trình được tạo sẵn từ trước. Với MPM <emphasis>event</emphasis>, nó cũng sử dụng các thread, nhưng các kết nối không có tín hiệu gì (đặc biệt những cái được giữ chạy bởi tính năng HTTP <emphasis>keep-alive</emphasis>) được gửi lại cho một thread riêng quản lý."

msgid "The Falcot administrators also install <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libapache2-mod-php5</emphasis> so as to include the PHP support in Apache. This causes the default <emphasis>event</emphasis> MPM to be disabled, and <emphasis>prefork</emphasis> to be used instead, since PHP only works under that particular MPM."
msgstr "Các nhà quản trị hệ thống Falcot cũng cài <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libapache2-mod-php5</emphasis> để đưa hỗ trợ PHP vào trong Apache. Điều này làm cho MPM <emphasis>event</emphasis> ngầm định bị tắt đi, và <emphasis>prefork</emphasis> được đưa vào sử dụng thay thế, bởi PHP chỉ hoạt động với MPM đó mà thôi."

msgid "<emphasis>SECURITY</emphasis> Execution under the <literal>www-data</literal> user"
msgstr "<emphasis>AN NINH</emphasis> Thực thi dưới người dùng <literal>www-data</literal> "

msgid "<primary><literal>www-data</literal></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><literal>www-data</literal></primary>"

msgid "<primary>suexec</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>suexec</primary>"

msgid "By default, Apache handles incoming requests under the identity of the <literal>www-data</literal> user. This means that a security vulnerability in a CGI script executed by Apache (for a dynamic page) won't compromise the whole system, but only the files owned by this particular user."
msgstr "Theo ngầm định, Apache xử lý các yêu cầu đến dưới quyền người dùng của tài khoản <literal>www-data</literal>. Điều này nghĩa là một lỗ hổng bảo mật trong một đoạn mã kịch bản CGI thực thi bởi Apache (cho một trang web động) sẽ không làm lộ cả một hệ thống, nhưng chỉ nhưng tập tin được sở hữu bởi người sử dụng này."

msgid "Using the <emphasis>suexec</emphasis> modules allows bypassing this rule so that some CGI scripts are executed under the identity of another user. This is configured with a <literal>SuexecUserGroup <replaceable>user</replaceable><replaceable>group</replaceable></literal> directive in the Apache configuration."
msgstr "Sử dụng các mô-đun <emphasis>suexec</emphasis> cho phép vượt qua quy tắc này để một số đoạn mã CGI được thực thi dưới quyền người dùng của một tài khoản khác. Điều này được cấu hình bởi chỉ thị <literal>SuexecUserGroup <replaceable>user</replaceable><replaceable>group</replaceable></literal> trong cấu hình Apache."

msgid "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">libapache2-mpm-itk</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">libapache2-mpm-itk</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "Another possibility is to use a dedicated MPM, such as the one provided by <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libapache2-mpm-itk</emphasis>. This particular one has a slightly different behavior: it allows “isolating” virtual hosts (actually, sets of pages) so that they each run as a different user. A vulnerability in one website therefore cannot compromise files belonging to the owner of another website."
msgstr "Một khả năng khác là sử dụng một MPM chuyên dụng, như là cái được cung cấp bởi <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libapache2-mpm-itk</emphasis>. Cái này có một hành vi hoàn toàn khác: nó cho phép “cách ly“ các máy ảo(virtual hosts) (thực ra, những tập hợp các trang) để mỗi cái trong số đó chạy dưới một người sử dụng khác nhau. Một lỗ hổng khác trong một trang web vì thế sẽ không thể làm lộ các tập tin thuộc về người sở hữu của trang web khác."

msgid "<emphasis>QUICK LOOK</emphasis> List of modules"
msgstr "<emphasis>SƠ LƯỢC</emphasis> Danh sách các mô-đun"

msgid "The full list of Apache standard modules can be found online. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/index.html\" />"
msgstr "Danh sách đầy đủ của các mô-đun chuẩn của Apache có thể tìm thấy trên mạng. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/index.html\" />"

msgid "Apache is a modular server, and many features are implemented by external modules that the main program loads during its initialization. The default configuration only enables the most common modules, but enabling new modules is a simple matter of running <command>a2enmod <replaceable>module</replaceable></command>; to disable a module, the command is <command>a2dismod <replaceable>module</replaceable></command>. These programs actually only create (or delete) symbolic links in <filename>/etc/apache2/mods-enabled/</filename>, pointing at the actual files (stored in <filename>/etc/apache2/mods-available/</filename>)."
msgstr "Apache là một máy phục vụ cấu thành bởi nhiều mô-đun, và nhiều tính năng của nó được tạo ra bởi những mô-đun bên ngoài mà chương trình chính sẽ thực thi trong quá trình khởi động. Cấu hình ngầm định chỉ kích hoạt các mô-đun phổ biến nhất, nhưng để kích hoạt các mô-đun mới này chỉ cần đơn giản chạy lệnh <command>a2enmod <replaceable>module</replaceable></command>; để tắt một mô-đun, lệnh là <command>a2dismod <replaceable>module</replaceable></command>. Những chương trình này thực ra chỉ tạo (hoặc xóa) các đường link tượng trưng(symbolic links) trong <filename>/etc/apache2/mods-enabled/</filename>, vốn chỉ đến những tập tin thực sự (lưu trong <filename>/etc/apache2/mods-available/</filename>)."

msgid "With its default configuration, the web server listens on port 80 (as configured in <filename>/etc/apache2/ports.conf</filename>), and serves pages from the <filename>/var/www/html/</filename> directory (as configured in <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-enabled/000-default.conf</filename>)."
msgstr "Với cấu hình ngầm định của nó, máy phục vụ web lắng nghe trên cổng 80 (như được cấu hình trong tập tin <filename>/etc/apache2/ports.conf</filename>), và phục vụ các trang  nằm trong thư mục <filename>/var/www/html/</filename> (như được cấu hình trong tập tin <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-enabled/000-default.conf</filename>)."

msgid "<emphasis>GOING FURTHER</emphasis> Adding support for SSL"
msgstr "<emphasis>TÌM HIỂU THÊM</emphasis> Thêm hỗ trợ cho SSL"

msgid "<primary>HTTPS</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>HTTPS</primary>"

msgid "<primary>HTTP</primary><secondary>secure</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>HTTP</primary><secondary>an ninh</secondary>"

msgid "Apache 2.4 includes the SSL module required for secure HTTP (HTTPS) out of the box. It just needs to be enabled with <command>a2enmod ssl</command>, then the required directives have to be added to the configuration files. A configuration example is provided in <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available/default-ssl.conf</filename>. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_ssl.html\" />"
msgstr "Apache 2.4 có sẵn một mô-đun SSL buộc phải có để hỗ trợ HTTP an toàn (HTTPS). Nó chỉ cần được kích hoạt với lệnh <command>a2enmod ssl</command>, sau đó các chỉ thị buộc phải có phải được thêm vào các tập tin cấu hình. Một ví dụ cấu hình được cung cấp trong <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available/default-ssl.conf</filename>. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_ssl.html\" />"

msgid "Some extra care must be taken if you want to favor SSL connections with <emphasis>Perfect Forward Secrecy</emphasis> (those connections use ephemeral session keys ensuring that a compromission of the server's secret key does not result in the compromission of old encrypted traffic that could have been stored while sniffing on the network). Have a look at Mozilla's recommandations in particular: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://wiki.mozilla.org/Security/Server_Side_TLS#Apache\" />"
msgstr "Phải cẩn thận hơn nếu bạn muốn ưu tiên các kết nối SSL với <emphasis>Bí mật Chiều đi Hoàn hảo(Perfect Forward Secrecy)</emphasis> (những kết nối sử dụng các mã phiên làm việc tạm thời để đảm bảo rằng việc lộ mã bí mật của máy phục vụ không dẫn đến việc lộ thông tin cũ đã được mã hóa vốn có thể bị lưu lại trước đây khi có ai nghe lén trên đường truyền). Quan sát các đề xuất của Mozilla, cụ thể là ở <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://wiki.mozilla.org/Security/Server_Side_TLS#Apache\" />"

msgid "<primary><emphasis>Perfect Forward Secrecy</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>Bí mật Chiều đi Hoàn hảo(Perfect Forward Secrecy)</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "Configuring Virtual Hosts"
msgstr "Cấu hình các máy ảo"

msgid "A virtual host is an extra identity for the web server."
msgstr "Một máy ảo là một danh xưng thêm cho một máy phục vụ."

msgid "<primary>virtual host</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>máy ảo</primary>"

msgid "Apache considers two different kinds of virtual hosts: those that are based on the IP address (or the port), and those that rely on the domain name of the web server. The first method requires allocating a different IP address (or port) for each site, whereas the second one can work on a single IP address (and port), and the sites are differentiated by the hostname sent by the HTTP client (which only works in version 1.1 of the HTTP protocol — fortunately that version is old enough that all clients use it already)."
msgstr "Apache có hai loại máy ảo khác nhau: một loại dựa trên địa chỉ IP (hoặc cổng), và một loại dựa trên tên miền của máy phục vụ web. Phương thức đầu tiên cần tạo một địa chỉ IP khác nhau (hay cổng) cho mỗi trang, trong khi phương thức số hai có thể hoạt động với một địa chỉ IP (và cổng) duy nhất, và những trang phân biệt bởi tên máy gửi bởi chương trình khách HTTP (vốn chỉ hoạt động tốt với phiên bản 1.1 của nghi thức HTTP - may mắn rằng phiên bản này đủ lâu để tất cả các chương trình khách đã sử dụng nó lâu rồi)."

msgid "The (increasing) scarcity of IPv4 addresses usually favors the second method; however, it is made more complex if the virtual hosts need to provide HTTPS too, since the SSL protocol hasn't always provided for name-based virtual hosting; the SNI extension (<emphasis>Server Name Indication</emphasis>) that allows such a combination is not handled by all browsers. When several HTTPS sites need to run on the same server, they will usually be differentiated either by running on a different port or on a different IP address (IPv6 can help there)."
msgstr "Sự khan hiếm ngày càng tăng của các địa chỉ IPv4 dẫn đến sự ưu tiên của phương thức số hai; tuy nhiên, nó được làm cho phức tạp hơn nếu các máy ảo cần cung cung cấp HTTPS, bởi vì giao thức SSL không luôn luôn cung cấp lưu trữ ảo dựa trên tên; phần mở rộng SNI (<emphasis>Tín hiệu chọn tên (Server Name Indication)</emphasis>) vốn cho phép một sự kết hợp như vậy không được xử lý bởi tất cả trình duyệt. Khi vào trang HTTPS cần chạy trên cùng một máy phục vụ, chúng sẽ được phân biệt bằng việc chạy trên một cổng riêng biệt hoặc chạy trên một địa chỉ IP riêng biệt (IPv6 có thể giúp ích ở đây)."

msgid "The default configuration for Apache 2 enables name-based virtual hosts. In addition, a default virtual host is defined in the <literal>/etc/apache2/sites-enabled/000-default.conf</literal> file; this virtual host will be used if no host matching the request sent by the client is found."
msgstr "Cấu hình ngầm định của Apache 2 cho phép các máy ảo dựa trên tên. Hơn nữa, một máy phục vụ ngầm định được định nghĩa trong tập tin <literal>/etc/apache2/sites-enabled/000-default.conf</literal>; máy ảo này sẽ được sử dụng nếu không máy được tìm thấy nào hợp với yêu cầu gửi bởi khách. "

msgid "<emphasis>CAUTION</emphasis> First virtual host"
msgstr "<emphasis>CẢNH BÁO</emphasis> Máy ảo đầu tiên"

msgid "Requests concerning unknown virtual hosts will always be served by the first defined virtual host, which is why we defined <literal>www.falcot.com</literal> first here."
msgstr "Những yêu cầu liên quan tới những máy ảo sẽ luôn được phục vụ bởi máy ảo ngầm định đầu tiên. Đó là lý do chúng ta định nghĩa <literal>www.falcot.com</literal> đầu tiên ở đây."

msgid "<emphasis>QUICK LOOK</emphasis> Apache supports SNI"
msgstr "<emphasis>SƠ LƯỢC</emphasis> Apache hỗ trợ SNI"

msgid "<primary>Server Name Indication</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Tín hiệu chọn tên (Server Name Indication)</primary>"

msgid "The Apache server supports an SSL protocol extension called <emphasis>Server Name Indication</emphasis> (SNI). This extension allows the browser to send the hostname of the web server during the establishment of the SSL connection, much earlier than the HTTP request itself, which was previously used to identify the requested virtual host among those hosted on the same server (with the same IP address and port). This allows Apache to select the most appropriate SSL certificate for the transaction to proceed."
msgstr "Máy phục vụ Apache hỗ trợ một phần mở rộng của nghi thức SSL được gọi là <emphasis>Tín hiệu chọn tên(Server Name Indication)</emphasis> (SNI). Phần mở rộng cho phép trình duyệt gửi tên máy của một máy phục vụ trong quá trình thiết lập kết nối SSL, sớm hơn nhiều so với chính yêu cầu HTTP, vốn được sử dụng trước đó để nhận dạng máy ảo được yêu cầu trong những máy được lưu trữ trên cùng một máy phục vụ (với cùng một địa chỉ IP và cổng). Điều này cho phép Apache chọn chứng chỉ SSL phù hợp nhất để tiếp tục giao dịch."

msgid "Before SNI, Apache would always use the certificate defined in the default virtual host. Clients trying to access another virtual host would then display warnings, since the certificate they received didn't match the website they were trying to access. Fortunately, most browsers now work with SNI; this includes Microsoft Internet Explorer starting with version 7.0 (starting on Vista), Mozilla Firefox starting with version 2.0, Apple Safari since version 3.2.1, and all versions of Google Chrome."
msgstr "Trước SNI, Apache sẽ luôn sử dụng chứng chỉ được định nghĩa trong máy ảo ngầm định. Các máy khách cố gắng truy cập một máy ảo khác sẽ hiển thị các cảnh báo, bởi chứng chỉ chúng nhận được không hợp với trang web họ đang cố gắng truy cập. May mắn thay, đa số trình duyệt bây giờ làm việc với SNI; chúng bao gồm Microsoft Internet Explorer bắt đầu với phiên bản 7.0 (trên Vista), Mozilla Firefox bắt đầu với phiên bản 2.0, Apple Safari từ phiên bản 3.2.1, và tất cả các phiên bản của Google Chrome."

msgid "The Apache package provided in Debian is built with support for SNI; no particular configuration is therefore needed."
msgstr "Gói phần mềm Apache cung cấp bởi Debian được xây dựng với hỗ trợ cho SNI; vì thế không cấu hình cụ thể nào là cần thiết."

msgid "Care should also be taken to ensure that the configuration for the first virtual host (the one used by default) does enable TLSv1, since Apache uses the parameters of this first virtual host to establish secure connections, and they had better allow them!"
msgstr "Phải cẩn thận hơn trong việc đảm bảo rằng cấu hình cho máy ảo đầu tiên (cái được sử dụng ngầm định) kích hoạt TLSv1, bởi Apache dùng các tham số của máy ảo ngầm định đầu tiên để thiết lập các kết nối an toàn, và các kết nối này tốt hơn là nên cho phép chúng."

msgid "Each extra virtual host is then described by a file stored in <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available/</filename>. Setting up a website for the <literal>falcot.org</literal> domain is therefore a simple matter of creating the following file, then enabling the virtual host with <command>a2ensite www.falcot.org</command>."
msgstr "Mỗi máy ảo thêm được mô tả bởi một tập tin được lưu trong <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available/</filename>. Vì thế, cài đặt một trang web cho miền <literal>falcot.org</literal> đơn giản chỉ là tạo một tập tin sau, sau đó kích hoạt máy ảo với lệnh <command>a2ensite www.falcot.org</command>."

msgid "The <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available/www.falcot.org.conf</filename> file"
msgstr "Tập tin <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available/www.falcot.org.conf</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;\n"
"ServerName www.falcot.org\n"
"ServerAlias falcot.org\n"
"DocumentRoot /srv/www/www.falcot.org\n"
"&lt;/VirtualHost&gt;"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;\n"
"ServerName www.falcot.org\n"
"ServerAlias falcot.org\n"
"DocumentRoot /srv/www/www.falcot.org\n"
"&lt;/VirtualHost&gt;"

msgid "The Apache server, as configured so far, uses the same log files for all virtual hosts (although this could be changed by adding <literal>CustomLog</literal> directives in the definitions of the virtual hosts). It therefore makes good sense to customize the format of this log file to have it include the name of the virtual host. This can be done by creating a <filename>/etc/apache2/conf-available/customlog.conf</filename> file that defines a new format for all log files (with the <literal>LogFormat</literal> directive) and by enabling it with <command>a2enconf customlog</command>. The <literal>CustomLog</literal> line must also be removed (or commented out) from the <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf</filename> file."
msgstr "Máy phục vụ Apache, như được cấu hình như trước đây, sử dụng chung những tập tin nhật ký cho tất cả các máy ảo (mặc dù điều này có thể được thay đổi bằng việc thêm các chỉ thị <literal>CustomLog</literal> vào các định nghĩa của các máy ảo). Vì thế sẽ có lý khi tùy chỉnh định dạng của tập tin nhật ký này để nhờ nó đính kèm tên của máy ảo. Điều này có thể được thực hiện bằng việc tạo một <filename>/etc/apache2/conf-available/customlog.conf</filename> vốn định nghĩa một định dạng mới cho tất cả các tập tin nhật ký (với chỉ thị <literal>LogFormat</literal>) và bằng việc kích hoạt nó với lệnh <command>a2enconf customlog</command>. Dòng <literal>CustomLog</literal> phải được xóa bỏ (hay chuyển thành ghi chú) khỏi tập tin <filename>/etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf</filename>."

msgid "The <filename>/etc/apache2/conf.d/customlog.conf</filename> file"
msgstr "Tập tin <filename>/etc/apache2/conf.d/customlog.conf</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"# New log format including (virtual) host name\n"
"LogFormat \"%v %h %l %u %t \\\"%r\\\" %&gt;s %b \\\"%{Referer}i\\\" \\\"%{User-Agent}i\\\"\" vhost\n"
"\n"
"# Now let's use this \"vhost\" format by default\n"
"CustomLog /var/log/apache2/access.log vhost"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"# Định dạng nhật ký mới bao gồm tên máy (ảo)\n"
"LogFormat \"%v %h %l %u %t \\\"%r\\\" %&gt;s %b \\\"%{Referer}i\\\" \\\"%{User-Agent}i\\\"\" vhost\n"
"\n"
"# Bây giờ hãy sử dụng định dạng \"vhost\" cho lựa chọn ngầm định\n"
"CustomLog /var/log/apache2/access.log vhost"

msgid "Common Directives"
msgstr "Các chỉ thị phổ biến"

msgid "This section briefly reviews some of the commonly-used Apache configuration directives."
msgstr "Phần này ôn lại một số chỉ thị của các chỉ thị cấu hình thường sử dụng của Apache."

msgid "<primary>Apache directives</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Các chỉ thị Apache</primary>"

msgid "<primary>directive, Apache</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>chỉ thị, Apache</primary>"

msgid "The main configuration file usually includes several <literal>Directory</literal> blocks; they allow specifying different behaviors for the server depending on the location of the file being served. Such a block commonly includes <literal>Options</literal> and <literal>AllowOverride</literal> directives."
msgstr "Tập tin cấu hình chính thường bao gồm các khối <literal>Directory</literal>; chúng cho phép chỉ định những hành vi khác nhau cho một máy phục vụ tùy theo địa chỉ của tập tin sẽ được phục vụ. Một khối như vậy thường bao gồm các chỉ thị <literal>Options</literal> và các chỉ thị <literal>AllowOverride</literal>."

msgid "<primary><literal>Options</literal>, Apache directive</primary>"
msgstr "<primary><literal>Options</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary>"

msgid "<primary><literal>AllowOverride</literal>, Apache directive</primary>"
msgstr "<primary><literal>AllowOverride</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary>"

msgid "Directory block"
msgstr "Khối thư mục (Directory block)"

msgid ""
"\n"
"&lt;Directory /var/www&gt;\n"
"Options Includes FollowSymlinks\n"
"AllowOverride All\n"
"DirectoryIndex index.php index.html index.htm\n"
"&lt;/Directory&gt;"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"&lt;Directory /var/www&gt;\n"
"Options Includes FollowSymlinks\n"
"AllowOverride All\n"
"DirectoryIndex index.php index.html index.htm\n"
"&lt;/Directory&gt;"

msgid "The <literal>DirectoryIndex</literal> directive contains a list of files to try when the client request matches a directory. The first existing file in the list is used and sent as a response."
msgstr "Chỉ thị <literal>DirectoryIndex</literal> bao gồm một danh sách các tập tin để thử khi yêu cầu từ chương trình khách hợp với một thư mục. Tập tin đầu tiên tồn tại trong danh sách sẽ được sử dụng và gửi đi như là một câu trả lời."

msgid "<primary><literal>DirectoryIndex</literal>, Apache directive</primary>"
msgstr "<primary><literal>DirectoryIndex</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary>"

msgid "The <literal>Options</literal> directive is followed by a list of options to enable. The <literal>None</literal> value disables all options; correspondingly, <literal>All</literal> enables them all except <literal>MultiViews</literal>. Available options include:"
msgstr "Chỉ thị <literal>Options</literal> được theo sau bởi một danh sách các lựa chọn để kích hoạt. Giá trị <literal>None</literal> tắt hết các lựa chọn; tương ứng, <literal>All</literal> kích hoạt tất cả ngoại trừ <literal>MultiViews</literal>. Các lựa chọn có sẵn bao gồm:"

msgid "<literal>ExecCGI</literal> indicates that CGI scripts can be executed. <indexterm><primary><literal>ExecCGI</literal>, Apache directive</primary></indexterm>"
msgstr "<literal>ExecCGI</literal> báo rằng các mã kịch bản CGI có thể được thực thi.  <indexterm><primary><literal>ExecCGI</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary></indexterm>"

msgid "<literal>FollowSymlinks</literal> tells the server that symbolic links can be followed, and that the response should contain the contents of the target of such links. <indexterm><primary><literal>FollowSymlinks</literal>, Apache directive</primary></indexterm>"
msgstr "<literal>FollowSymlinks</literal> cho máy phục vụ biết là các đường link tượng trưng (symbolic links) có thể dùng để tìm ra địa điểm, và câu trả lời nên chứa những nội dung ở địa điểm của các đường link đó.<indexterm><primary><literal>FollowSymlinks</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary></indexterm>"

msgid "<literal>SymlinksIfOwnerMatch</literal> also tells the server to follow symbolic links, but only when the link and the its target have the same owner. <indexterm><primary><literal>SymlinksIfOwnerMatch</literal>, Apache directive</primary></indexterm>"
msgstr "<literal>SymlinksIfOwnerMatch</literal> cũng bảo máy phục vụ đi theo các đường dẫn tượng trưng (symbolic links), nhưng chỉ khi đường dẫn và đích của nó có chung một người sở hữu. <indexterm><primary><literal>SymlinksIfOwnerMatch</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary></indexterm>"

msgid "<literal>Includes</literal> enables <emphasis>Server Side Includes</emphasis> (<emphasis>SSI</emphasis> for short). These are directives embedded in HTML pages and executed on the fly for each request. <indexterm><primary><literal>Includes</literal>, Apache directive</primary></indexterm>"
msgstr "<literal>Includes</literal> kích hoạt <emphasis>Các Hướng dẫn Kèm tập tin bên Máy phục vụ(Server Side Includes)</emphasis>(ngắn gọn là <emphasis>SSI</emphasis>). Những chỉ thị này được nhúng vào các trang HTML và thực thi theo yêu cầu. <indexterm><primary><literal>Includes</literal>, Apache directive</primary></indexterm>"

msgid "<literal>Indexes</literal> tells the server to list the contents of a directory if the HTTP request sent by the client points at a directory without an index file (ie, when no files mentioned by the <literal>DirectoryIndex</literal> directive exists in this directory). <indexterm><primary><literal>Indexes</literal>, Apache directive</primary></indexterm>"
msgstr "<literal>Indexes</literal> bảo máy phục vụ liệt kê nội dung của một thư mục nếu yêu cầu HTTP gửi bởi một chương trình khách chỉ đến một thư mục mà không có tập tin chỉ mục (index file) (nghĩa là khi không có tập tin nào được đề cập đến trong chỉ thị <literal>DirectoryIndex</literal> tồn tại trong thư mục này). <indexterm><primary><literal>Indexes</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary></indexterm>"

msgid "<literal>MultiViews</literal> enables content negotiation; this can be used by the server to return a web page matching the preferred language as configured in the browser. <indexterm><primary><literal>MultiViews</literal>, Apache directive</primary></indexterm>"
msgstr "<literal>MultiViews</literal> kích hoạt việc đàm phán về nội dung; điều này có thể được sử dụng bởi một máy phục vụ để trả về một trang web hợp với ngôn ngữ ưu tiên được cấu hình trong trình duyệt. <indexterm><primary><literal>MultiViews</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary></indexterm>"

msgid "<emphasis>BACK TO BASICS</emphasis> <filename>.htaccess</filename> file"
msgstr "<emphasis>TRỞ VỀ CƠ BẢN</emphasis> tập tin <filename>.htaccess</filename>"

msgid "The <filename>.htaccess</filename> file contains Apache configuration directives enforced each time a request concerns an element of the directory where it is stored. The scope of these directives also recurses to all the subdirectories within."
msgstr "Tập tin <filename>.htaccess</filename> chứa các chỉ thị cấu hình Apache được thực thi mỗi lần một yêu cầu cần đến một phần tử của một thư mục nơi nó được lưu. Phạm vi của những chỉ thị này sẽ đi sâu xuống các thư mục con bên trong nó."

msgid "<primary><filename>.htaccess</filename></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>.htaccess</filename></primary>"

msgid "Most of the directives that can occur in a <literal>Directory</literal> block are also legal in a <filename>.htaccess</filename> file."
msgstr "Đa số những chỉ thị có thể xảy ra trong khối <literal>Directory</literal> cũng hợp lệ trong tập tin <filename>.htaccess</filename>."

msgid "The <literal>AllowOverride</literal> directive lists all the options that can be enabled or disabled by way of a <filename>.htaccess</filename> file. A common use of this option is to restrict <literal>ExecCGI</literal>, so that the administrator chooses which users are allowed to run programs under the web server's identity (the <literal>www-data</literal> user)."
msgstr "Chỉ thị <literal>AllowOverride</literal> liệt kê tất cả những lựa chọn được kích hoạt hay được tắt bởi tập tin <filename>.htaccess</filename>. Một mục đích sử dụng của lựa chọn này là để giới hạn <literal>ExecCGI</literal>, để cho nhà quản trị hệ thống lựa chọn những người sử dụng nào được cho phép chạy các chương trình dưới danh xưng của máy phục vụ web (tài khoản <literal>www-data</literal>)."

msgid "Requiring Authentication"
msgstr "Ràng buộc Chứng thực"

msgid "<primary>web authentication</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>chứng thực web</primary>"

msgid "In some circumstances, access to part of a website needs to be restricted, so only legitimate users who provide a username and a password are granted access to the contents."
msgstr "Trong một số trường hợp, truy cập tới một phần của một trang web cần phải được giới hạn, để chỉ có những người sử dụng hợp lệ có tên tài khoản và mật mã mới được cho phép truy cập nội dung."

msgid "<filename>.htaccess</filename> file requiring authentication"
msgstr "Tập tin <filename>.htaccess</filename> bắt buộc chứng thực"

msgid ""
"\n"
"Require valid-user\n"
"AuthName \"Private directory\"\n"
"AuthType Basic\n"
"AuthUserFile /etc/apache2/authfiles/htpasswd-private"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Require valid-user\n"
"AuthName \"Private directory\"\n"
"AuthType Basic\n"
"AuthUserFile /etc/apache2/authfiles/htpasswd-private"

msgid "<emphasis>SECURITY</emphasis> No security"
msgstr "<emphasis>AN NINH</emphasis> Không an toàn"

msgid "The authentication system used in the above example (<literal>Basic</literal>) has minimal security as the password is sent in clear text (it is only encoded as <emphasis>base64</emphasis>, which is a simple encoding rather than an encryption method). It should also be noted that the documents “protected” by this mechanism also go over the network in the clear. If security is important, the whole HTTP connection should be encrypted with SSL."
msgstr "Hệ thống chứng thực sử dụng trong ví dụ trên (<literal>Basic</literal>) có độ an toàn rất thấp bởi mật mã được gửi đi dưới dạng chữ (nó chỉ được mã hóa dưới dạng  <emphasis>base64</emphasis>, vốn là một dạng mã đơn giản hơn là một phương thức mã hóa). Cũng cần phải ghi chú rằng những tài liệu “được bảo vệ” bởi cơ chế này cũng di chuyển trên mạng không có ai trông coi. Nếu an ninh cần được coi trọng, toàn bộ kết nối HTTP nên được mã hóa với SSL."

msgid "The <filename>/etc/apache2/authfiles/htpasswd-private</filename> file contains a list of users and passwords; it is commonly manipulated with the <command>htpasswd</command> command. For example, the following command is used to add a user or change their password: <indexterm><primary><command>htpasswd</command></primary></indexterm>"
msgstr "Tập tin <filename>/etc/apache2/authfiles/htpasswd-private</filename> chứa một danh sách các tên tài khoản và mật mã; nó thường được chỉnh sửa bởi lệnh <command>htpasswd</command>. Ví dụ, lệnh sau được sử dụng để thêm một tài khoản hoặc thay đổi mật mã: <indexterm><primary><command>htpasswd</command></primary></indexterm>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"<computeroutput># </computeroutput><userinput>htpasswd /etc/apache2/authfiles/htpasswd-private <replaceable>user</replaceable>\n"
"</userinput><computeroutput>New password:\n"
"Re-type new password:\n"
"Adding password for user <replaceable>user</replaceable>\n"
"</computeroutput>"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<computeroutput># </computeroutput><userinput>htpasswd /etc/apache2/authfiles/htpasswd-private <replaceable>user</replaceable>\n"
"</userinput><computeroutput>Mật mã mới:\n"
"Nhập lại mật mã mới:\n"
"Thêm mật mã cho tài khoản <replaceable>user</replaceable>\n"
"</computeroutput>"

msgid "Restricting Access"
msgstr "Giới hạn truy cập"

msgid "<primary>web access restriction</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Giới hạn truy cập web</primary>"

msgid "The <literal>Require</literal> directive controls access restrictions for a directory (and its subdirectories, recursively)."
msgstr "Chỉ thị <literal>Require</literal> kiểm soát các giới hạn truy cập cho một thư mục (và những thư mục con, và tiếp tục như vậy cho chúng)."

msgid "<primary><literal>Require</literal>, Apache directive</primary>"
msgstr "<primary><literal>Require</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary>"

msgid "It can be used to restrict access based on many criteria; we will stop at describing access restriction based on the IP address of the client, but it can be made much more powerful than that, especially when several <literal>Require</literal> directives are combined within a <literal>RequireAll</literal> block."
msgstr "Nó có thể được sử dụng để giới hạn truy cập dựa trên nhiều điều kiện; chúng ta sẽ ngưng tại việc mô tả giới hạn truy cập dựa trên địa chỉ IP của chương trình khách, nhưng nó có thể được làm cho mạnh hơn thế, đặc biệt khi vài chỉ thị <literal>Require</literal> được kết hợp trong một khối <literal>RequireAll</literal>."

msgid "Only allow from the local network"
msgstr "Chỉ cho phép từ mạng nội bộ"

msgid "Require ip 192.168.0.0/16"
msgstr "Require ip 192.168.0.0/16"

msgid "<emphasis>ALTERNATIVE</emphasis> Old syntax"
msgstr "<emphasis>LỰA CHỌN THAY THẾ</emphasis> Cú pháp cũ"

msgid "The <literal>Require</literal> syntax is only available in Apache 2.4 (the version in <emphasis role=\"distribution\">Jessie</emphasis>). For users of <emphasis role=\"distribution\">Wheezy</emphasis>, the Apache 2.2 syntax is different, and we describe it here mainly for reference, although it can also be made available in Apache 2.4 using the <literal>mod_access_compat</literal> module."
msgstr "Cú pháp <literal>Require</literal> chỉ tồn tại trong Apache 2.4 (phiên bản có trong <emphasis role=\"distribution\">Jessie</emphasis>). Với những người sử dụng của <emphasis role=\"distribution\">Wheezy</emphasis>, cú pháp Apache 2.2 rất khác biệt, và chúng ta mô tả nó ở đây chủ yếu để tham khảo, mặc dù nó có thể được hỗ trợ trong Apache 2.4 bằng mô-đun <literal>mod_access_compat</literal>."

msgid "The <literal>Allow from</literal> and <literal>Deny from</literal> directives control access restrictions for a directory (and its subdirectories, recursively)."
msgstr "Các chỉ thị <literal>Allow from</literal> và <literal>Deny from</literal> kiểm soát các giới hạn truy cập cho một thư mục (và các thư mục con, và lại tiếp tục như vậy)."

msgid "<primary><literal>Allow from</literal>, Apache directive</primary>"
msgstr "<primary><literal>Allow from</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary>"

msgid "<primary><literal>Deny from</literal>, Apache directive</primary>"
msgstr "<primary><literal>Deny from</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary>"

msgid "<primary><literal>Order</literal>, Apache directive</primary>"
msgstr "<primary><literal>Order</literal>, chỉ thị Apache</primary>"

msgid "The <literal>Order</literal> directive tells the server of the order in which the <literal>Allow from</literal> and <literal>Deny from</literal> directives are applied; the last one that matches takes precedence. In concrete terms, <literal>Order deny,allow</literal> allows access if no <literal>Deny from</literal> applies, or if an <literal>Allow from</literal> directive does. Conversely, <literal>Order allow,deny</literal> rejects access if no <literal>Allow from</literal> directive matches (or if a <literal>Deny from</literal> directive applies)."
msgstr "Chỉ thị <literal>Order</literal> cho máy phục vụ biết rằng thứ tự thực thi các chỉ thị <literal>Allow from</literal> và <literal>Deny from</literal>; chỉ thị nằm cuối cùng và phải khớp được ưu tiên trước. Cụ thể hơn, <literal>Order deny,allow</literal> cho phép truy cập nếu không có <literal>Deny from</literal> nào áp dụng được, hoặc nếu một chỉ thị <literal>Allow from</literal> áp dụng được. Ngược lại, <literal>Order allow,deny</literal> từ chối truy cập nếu không có chỉ thị <literal>Allow from</literal> nào khớp (hoặc nếu một chỉ thị <literal>Deny from</literal> áp dụng được)."

msgid "The <literal>Allow from</literal> and <literal>Deny from</literal> directives can be followed by an IP address, a network (such as <literal>192.168.0.0/255.255.255.0</literal>, <literal>192.168.0.0/24</literal> or even <literal>192.168.0</literal>), a hostname or a domain name, or the <literal>all</literal> keyword, designating everyone."
msgstr "Các chỉ thị <literal>Allow from</literal> và <literal>Deny from</literal> có thể được theo sau bởi một địa chỉ IP, một dãy số cho vùng mạng (như là <literal>192.168.0.0/255.255.255.0</literal>, <literal>192.168.0.0/24</literal> or even <literal>192.168.0</literal>), một tên máy hoặc một tên miền, hoặc từ khóa <literal>all</literal>, ám chỉ bất cứ ai."

msgid "For instance, to reject connections by default but allow them from the local network, you could use this:"
msgstr "Ví dụ, để từ chối các kết nối theo ngầm định nhưng cho phép chúng từ mạng nội bộ, bạn có thể làm như sau:"

msgid ""
"\n"
"Order deny,allow\n"
"Allow from 192.168.0.0/16\n"
"Deny from all"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Order deny,allow\n"
"Allow from 192.168.0.0/16\n"
"Deny from all"

msgid "Log Analyzers"
msgstr "Các chương trình phân tích nhật ký"

msgid "A log analyzer is frequently installed on a web server; since the former provides the administrators with a precise idea of the usage patterns of the latter."
msgstr "Một chương trình phân tích nhật ký thường được cài đặt trên một máy phục vụ web; bởi chương trình phân tích cung cấp cho các quản trị viên một cái nhìn chính xác về quy luật hoạt động của máy phục vụ web."

msgid "The Falcot Corp administrators selected <emphasis>AWStats</emphasis> (<emphasis>Advanced Web Statistics</emphasis>) to analyze their Apache log files."
msgstr "Các nhà quản trị hệ thống Công ty Falcot đã lựa chọn <emphasis>AWStats</emphasis> (<emphasis>Advanced Web Statistics (Thông số Web Chuyên sâu)</emphasis>) để phân tích các tập tin nhật ký Apache."

msgid "<primary><emphasis>AWStats</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>AWStats</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "<primary>web logs analyzer</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>chương trình phân tích các nhật ký web</primary>"

msgid "<primary>logs</primary><secondary>web logs analyzer</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>logs</primary><secondary>chương trình phân tích các nhật ký web</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>analyzer of web logs</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>chương trình phân tích các nhật ký web</primary>"

msgid "The first configuration step is the customization of the <filename>/etc/awstats/awstats.conf</filename> file. The Falcot administrators keep it unchanged apart from the following parameters:"
msgstr "Bước cấu hình đầu tiên là tùy chỉnh tập tin <filename>/etc/awstats/awstats.conf</filename>. Các nhà quản trị hê thống của Falcot giữ phần không thay đổi của nó khỏi các thông số sau đây:"

msgid ""
"\n"
"LogFile=\"/var/log/apache2/access.log\"\n"
"LogFormat = \"%virtualname %host %other %logname %time1 %methodurl %code %bytesd %refererquot %uaquot\"\n"
"SiteDomain=\"www.falcot.com\"\n"
"HostAliases=\"falcot.com REGEX[^.*\\.falcot\\.com$]\"\n"
"DNSLookup=1\n"
"LoadPlugin=\"tooltips\""
msgstr ""
"\n"
"LogFile=\"/var/log/apache2/access.log\"\n"
"LogFormat = \"%virtualname %host %other %logname %time1 %methodurl %code %bytesd %refererquot %uaquot\"\n"
"SiteDomain=\"www.falcot.com\"\n"
"HostAliases=\"falcot.com REGEX[^.*\\.falcot\\.com$]\"\n"
"DNSLookup=1\n"
"LoadPlugin=\"tooltips\""

msgid "All these parameters are documented by comments in the template file. In particular, the <varname>LogFile</varname> and <varname>LogFormat</varname> parameters describe the location and format of the log file and the information it contains; <varname>SiteDomain</varname> and <varname>HostAliases</varname> list the various names under which the main web site is known."
msgstr "Tất cả những thông số này đuợc ghi chú trong tập tin mẫu(template). Cụ thể hơn, các thông số  <varname>LogFile</varname> và <varname>LogFormat</varname> mô tả địa điểm và định dạng của tập tin nhật ký và thông tin chứa đựng trong nó; <varname>SiteDomain</varname> và <varname>HostAliases</varname> liệt kê những cái tên mà trang web chính thức được biết tới."

msgid "For high traffic sites, <varname>DNSLookup</varname> should usually not be set to <literal>1</literal>; for smaller sites, such as the Falcot one described above, this setting allows getting more readable reports that include full machine names instead of raw IP addresses."
msgstr "Đối với những trang web có lưu lượng truyền tải cao, <varname>DNSLookup</varname> thuờng không nên được cài đặt giá trị <literal>1</literal>; cho những trang nhỏ, như cái Falcot được mô tả phía trên, cài đặt này cho phép thu thập nhiều bản báo cáo dễ đọc hơn vốn bao gồm những tên máy đầy đủ thay vì các địa chỉ IP thô."

msgid "<emphasis>SECURITY</emphasis> Access to statistics"
msgstr "<emphasis>AN NINH</emphasis> Truy cập tới các thông số"

msgid "AWStats makes its statistics available on the website with no restrictions by default, but restrictions can be set up so that only a few (probably internal) IP addresses can access them; the list of allowed IP addresses needs to be defined in the <varname>AllowAccessFromWebToFollowingIPAddresses</varname> parameter"
msgstr "AWStats công bố các thông số của nó trên trang web mà không có giới hạn gì theo ngầm định, nhưng các giới hạn có thể được đặt ra để một số địa chỉ IP (có thể nội bộ) có thể truy cập chúng; danh sách các địa chỉ IP được cho phép cần phải được định nghĩa lại trong tham số <varname>AllowAccessFromWebToFollowingIPAddresses</varname>"

msgid "AWStats will also be enabled for other virtual hosts; each virtual host needs its own configuration file, such as <filename>/etc/awstats/awstats.www.falcot.org.conf</filename>."
msgstr "AWStats sẽ được kích hoạt cho các máy ảo(virtual host) khác;mỗi máy ảo cần có một tập tin cấu hình riêng, như là <filename>/etc/awstats/awstats.www.falcot.org.conf</filename>."

msgid "AWStats configuration file for a virtual host"
msgstr "Tập tin cấu hình AWStats cho một máy ảo(virtual host)"

msgid ""
"\n"
"Include \"/etc/awstats/awstats.conf\"\n"
"SiteDomain=\"www.falcot.org\"\n"
"HostAliases=\"falcot.org\""
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Include \"/etc/awstats/awstats.conf\"\n"
"SiteDomain=\"www.falcot.org\"\n"
"HostAliases=\"falcot.org\""

msgid "AWStats uses many icons stored in the <filename>/usr/share/awstats/icon/</filename> directory. In order for these icons to be available on the web site, the Apache configuration needs to be adapted to include the following directive:"
msgstr "AWStats sử dụng nhiều biểu tượng lưu trong thư mục <filename>/usr/share/awstats/icon/</filename>. Để những biểu tượng này có thể được truy cập bởi trang web, cấu hình Apache cần được chỉnh sửa để bao gồm chỉ thị sau đây:"

msgid ""
"\n"
"Alias /awstats-icon/ /usr/share/awstats/icon/"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Alias /awstats-icon/ /usr/share/awstats/icon/"

msgid "After a few minutes (and once the script has been run a few times), the results are available online: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://www.falcot.com/cgi-bin/awstats.pl\" /><ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://www.falcot.org/cgi-bin/awstats.pl\" />"
msgstr "Sau một vài phút (và khi đoạn mã được chạy vài lần), các kết quả nằm sẵn trên mạng: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://www.falcot.com/cgi-bin/awstats.pl\" /><ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://www.falcot.org/cgi-bin/awstats.pl\" />"

msgid "<emphasis>CAUTION</emphasis> Log file rotation"
msgstr "<emphasis>CẢNH BÁO</emphasis> Quay vòng các tập tin nhật ký"

msgid "In order for the statistics to take all the logs into account, <emphasis>AWStats</emphasis> needs to be run right before the Apache log files are rotated. Looking at the <literal>prerotate</literal> directive of <filename>/etc/logrotate.d/apache2</filename> file, this can be solved by putting a symlink to <filename>/usr/share/awstats/tools/update.sh</filename> in <filename>/etc/logrotate.d/httpd-prerotate</filename>:"
msgstr "Để những thông số này tính luôn cả các tập tin nhật ký, <emphasis>AWStats</emphasis> cần được chạy ngay trước khi các tập tin nhật ký được xoay vòng. Xem chỉ thị <literal>prerotate</literal> của tập tin <filename>/etc/logrotate.d/apache2</filename>, điều này có thể được giải quyết bằng việc đặt một đường link tượng trưng vào <filename>/usr/share/awstats/tools/update.sh</filename> vào <filename>/etc/logrotate.d/httpd-prerotate</filename>:"

msgid ""
"<computeroutput>$ </computeroutput><userinput>cat /etc/logrotate.d/apache2\n"
"</userinput><computeroutput>/var/log/apache2/*.log {\n"
"  daily\n"
"  missingok\n"
"  rotate 14\n"
"  compress\n"
"  delaycompress\n"
"  notifempty\n"
"  create 644 root adm\n"
"  sharedscripts\n"
"  postrotate\n"
"    if /etc/init.d/apache2 status &gt; /dev/null ; then \\\n"
"      /etc/init.d/apache2 reload &gt; /dev/null; \\\n"
"    fi;\n"
"  endscript\n"
"  prerotate\n"
"    if [ -d /etc/logrotate.d/httpd-prerotate ]; then \\\n"
"      run-parts /etc/logrotate.d/httpd-prerotate; \\\n"
"    fi; \\\n"
"  endscript\n"
"}\n"
"$ </computeroutput><userinput>sudo mkdir -p /etc/logrotate.d/httpd-prerotate\n"
"</userinput><computeroutput>$ </computeroutput><userinput>sudo ln -sf /usr/share/awstats/tools/update.sh \\\n"
"  /etc/logrotate.d/httpd-prerotate/awstats\n"
"</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<computeroutput>$ </computeroutput><userinput>cat /etc/logrotate.d/apache2\n"
"</userinput><computeroutput>/var/log/apache2/*.log {\n"
"  daily\n"
"  missingok\n"
"  rotate 14\n"
"  compress\n"
"  delaycompress\n"
"  notifempty\n"
"  create 644 root adm\n"
"  sharedscripts\n"
"  postrotate\n"
"    if /etc/init.d/apache2 status &gt; /dev/null ; then \\\n"
"      /etc/init.d/apache2 reload &gt; /dev/null; \\\n"
"    fi;\n"
"  endscript\n"
"  prerotate\n"
"    if [ -d /etc/logrotate.d/httpd-prerotate ]; then \\\n"
"      run-parts /etc/logrotate.d/httpd-prerotate; \\\n"
"    fi; \\\n"
"  endscript\n"
"}\n"
"$ </computeroutput><userinput>sudo mkdir -p /etc/logrotate.d/httpd-prerotate\n"
"</userinput><computeroutput>$ </computeroutput><userinput>sudo ln -sf /usr/share/awstats/tools/update.sh \\\n"
"  /etc/logrotate.d/httpd-prerotate/awstats\n"
"</userinput>"

msgid "Note also that the log files created by <command>logrotate</command> need to be readable by everyone, especially AWStats. In the above example, this is ensured by the <literal>create 644 root adm</literal> line (instead of the default <literal>640</literal> permissions)."
msgstr "Ghi chú rằng các tập tin nhật ký tạo ra bởi lệnh <command>logrotate</command> cần có thể được đọc bởi mọi người, đặc biệt là AWStats. Trong ví dụ trên, điều này được đảm bảo bằng dòng <literal>create 644 root adm</literal> (thay vì mã truy cập <literal>640</literal> ngầm định)."

msgid "FTP File Server"
msgstr "Máy phục vụ Tập tin FTP"

msgid "<primary>FTP (<emphasis>File Transfer Protocol</emphasis>)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>FTP (<emphasis>Giao thức chuyển tải tập tin</emphasis>)</primary>"

msgid "FTP (<emphasis>File Transfer Protocol</emphasis>) is one of the first protocols of the Internet (RFC 959 was issued in 1985!). It was used to distribute files before the Web was even born (the HTTP protocol was created in 1990, and formally defined in its 1.0 version by RFC 1945, issued in 1996)."
msgstr "FTP (<emphasis>Giao thức Chuyển tải Tập tin</emphasis>) là một trong những giao thức Internet (RFC 959 được tung ra vào năm 1985!). Nó được dùng để phân phối các tập tin trước khi Web được sinh ra (giao thức HTTP được tạo ra vào năm 1990, và được định nghĩa chính thức trong phiên bản 1.0 trong RFC 1945, tung ra năm 1996)."

msgid "This protocol allows both file uploads and file downloads; for this reason, it is still widely used to deploy updates to a website hosted by one's Internet service provider (or any other entity hosting websites). In these cases, secure access is enforced with a user identifier and password; on successful authentication, the FTP server grants read-write access to that user's home directory."
msgstr "Giao thức này cho phép cả tải lên và tải xuống; vì lí do này, nó vẫn được sử dụng rộng rãi để phân phối các bản cập nhật cho một trang web lưu trên nhà cung cấp dịch vụ Internet của một cá nhân nào đó(hoặc bất kì các trang web lưu trữ khác). Trong các trường hợp này, truy cập an toàn được đảm bảo với một tên tài khoản và mật mã; khi đăng nhập thành công, máy phục vụ FTP cho phép truy cập đọc-viết vào thư mục nhà của người sử dụng đó."

msgid "Other FTP servers are mainly used to distribute files for public downloading; Debian packages are a good example. The contents of these servers is fetched from other, geographically remote, servers; it is then made available to less distant users. This means that client authentication is not required; as a consequence, this operating mode is known as “anonymous FTP”. To be perfectly correct, the clients do authenticate with the <literal>anonymous</literal> username; the password is often, by convention, the user's email address, but the server ignores it."
msgstr "Các máy phục vụ FTP khác được sử dụng nhằm để phân phối các tập tin để tải xuống công cộng; các gói phần mềm Debian là một ví dụ tốt. Nội dung của những máy phục vụ được lấy về từ các máy phục vụ từ xa; sau đó nó được cung cấp cho các người dùng ít xa xôi hơn. Điều này nghĩa là chứng thực chương trình khách là không cần thiết; vì thế, chế độ hoạt động này được biết đến là “FTP ẩn danh“. Để nói cho thực sự chính xác, các khách hàng xác thực với tên tài khoản <literal>anonymous</literal>; mật mã thường là địa chỉ email của người sử dụng, nhưng máy phục vụ thường phớt lờ nó."

msgid "Many FTP servers are available in Debian (<emphasis role=\"pkg\">ftpd</emphasis>, <emphasis role=\"pkg\">proftpd-basic</emphasis>, <emphasis role=\"pkg\">pyftpd</emphasis> and so on). The Falcot Corp administrators picked <emphasis role=\"pkg\">vsftpd</emphasis> because they only use the FTP server to distribute a few files (including a Debian package repository); since they don't need advanced features, they chose to focus on the security aspects."
msgstr "Nhiều máy phục vụ FTP hiện đang có sẵn trong Debian (<emphasis role=\"pkg\">ftpd</emphasis>, <emphasis role=\"pkg\">proftpd-basic</emphasis>, <emphasis role=\"pkg\">pyftpd</emphasis> và vâng vâng). Các nhà quản trị hê thống của Công ty Falcot chọn <emphasis role=\"pkg\">vsftpd</emphasis> bởi họ chỉ sử dụng máy phục vụ FTP để phân phối một vài tập tin (bao gồm một kho gói phần mềm Debian); do họ không cần các tính năng phức tạp, họ chọn tập trung vào các mặt an ninh."

msgid "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">vsftpd</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">vsftpd</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "Installing the package creates an <literal>ftp</literal> system user. This account is always used for anonymous FTP connections, and its home directory (<filename>/srv/ftp/</filename>) is the root of the tree made available to users connecting to this service. The default configuration (in <filename>/etc/vsftpd.conf</filename>) requires some changes to cater to the simple need of making big files available for public downloads: anonymous access needs to be enabled (<literal>anonymous_enable=YES</literal>) and read-only access of local users needs to be disabled (<literal>local_enable=NO</literal>). The latter is particularly important since the FTP protocol doesn't use any form of encryption and the user password could be intercepted over the wire."
msgstr "Cài đặt gói phần mềm đó tạo một tài khoản hệ thống <literal>ftp</literal>. Tài khoản này luôn được sử dụng cho các kết nối FTP ẩn danh, và thư mục nhà của nó (<filename>/srv/ftp/</filename>) là gốc của cây thư mục được tạo sẵn cho các người sử dụng kết nối đến dịch vụ này. Cấu hình ngầm định (trong <filename>/etc/vsftpd.conf</filename>) buộc một vài thay đổi để hỗ trợ nhu cầu tạo ra các tập tin lớn để tải xuống công cộng: các kết nối ẩn danh cần được kích hoạt (<literal>anonymous_enable=YES</literal>) và kết nối chỉ đọc cho các người dùng cục bộ cần phải được tắt (<literal>local_enable=NO</literal>). Phần sau chỉ đặc biệt quan trọng bởi giao thức FTP không sử dụng bất cứ hình thức mã hóa nào và mật mã tài khoản có thể bị can thiệp trên đường truyền."

msgid "NFS File Server"
msgstr "Máy phục vụ tập tin NFS"

msgid "NFS (<emphasis>Network File System</emphasis>) is a protocol allowing remote access to a filesystem through the network. All Unix systems can work with this protocol; when Windows systems are involved, Samba must be used instead."
msgstr "NFS ("<emphasis>Hệ thống Tập tin Mạng(Network File System)</emphasis>) là một giao thức cho phép truy cập từ xa tới một hệ thống tập tin thông qua mạng. Tất cả các hệ thống Unix có thể làm việc với giao thức này; khi các hệ thống Windows có liên quan, Samba phải được sử dụng thay thế." 

msgid "<primary>NFS</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>NFS</primary>"

msgid "<primary><emphasis>Network</emphasis></primary><secondary><emphasis>File System</emphasis></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>Mạng</emphasis></primary><secondary><emphasis>Hệ thống Tập tin</emphasis></secondary>"

msgid "<primary>filesystem</primary><secondary>network</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>Hệ thống tập tin</primary><secondary>mạng</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>file</primary><secondary>server</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>tập tin</primary><secondary>máy phục vụ</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>server</primary><secondary>file</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>máy phục vụ</primary><secondary>tập tin</secondary>"

msgid "NFS is a very useful tool but, historically, it has suffered from many limitations, most of which have been addressed with version 4 of the protocol. The downside is that the latest version of NFS is harder to configure when you want to make use of basic security features such as authentication and encryption since it relies on Kerberos for those parts. And without those, the NFS protocol must be restricted to a trusted local network since data goes over the network unencrypted (a <emphasis>sniffer</emphasis> can intercept it) and access rights are granted based on the client's IP address (which can be spoofed)."
msgstr "NFS là một công cụ hữu dụng nhưng, theo lịch sử, nó đã hứng chịu nhiều giới hạn, đa số được giải quyết với phiên bản số 4 của giao thức này. Ngược lại, phiên bản mới nhất của NFS khó cấu hình hơn khi bạn muốn sử dụng các tính năng an ninh đơn giản ví dụ như xác thực và mã hóa bởi nó dựa trên Kerberos cho những thành phần đó. Và nếu không có những thứ trên, giao thức NFS phải được giới hạn lại trong một mạng lưới nội bộ đáng tin cậy bởi dữ liệu di chuyển trên mạng nội bộ mà không được mã hóa (một <emphasis>kẻ nghe lén(sniffer)</emphasis> có thể can thiệp nó) và quyền truy cập được cung cấp dựa trên địa chỉ IP của khách (vốn có thể được làm giả)."

msgid "<emphasis>DOCUMENTATION</emphasis> NFS HOWTO"
msgstr "<emphasis>TÀI LIỆU HƯỚNG DẪN</emphasis> HƯỚNG DẪN NFS"

msgid "Good documentation to deploy NFSv4 is rather scarce. Here are some pointers with content of varying quality but that should at least give some hints on what should be done. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://help.ubuntu.com/community/NFSv4Howto\" /> <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://wiki.linux-nfs.org/wiki/index.php/Nfsv4_configuration\" />"
msgstr "Tài liệu hướng dẫn có chất lượng để chạy NFSv4 thì khá khan hiếm. Đây là một vài nguồn với những nội dung có mức độ chi tiết khác nhau nhưng đó ít nhất sẽ cho bạn một số thông tin về những gì cần phải làm. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://help.ubuntu.com/community/NFSv4Howto\" /> <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://wiki.linux-nfs.org/wiki/index.php/Nfsv4_configuration\" />"

msgid "Securing NFS"
msgstr "Đảm bảo an ninh cho NFS"

msgid "<primary>NFS</primary><secondary>security</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>NFS</primary><secondary>an ninh</secondary>"

msgid "If you don't use the Kerberos-based security features, it is vital to ensure that only the machines allowed to use NFS can connect to the various required RPC servers, because the basic protocol trusts the data received from the network. The firewall must also block <emphasis>IP spoofing</emphasis> so as to prevent an outside machine from acting as an inside one, and access to the appropriate ports must be restricted to the machines meant to access the NFS shares."
msgstr "Nếu bạn không sử dụng các tính năng an ninh dựa trên Kerberos, sẽ rất quan trọng để đảm bảo rằng chỉ những máy được cho phép sử dụng NFS mới có thể kết nối tới các máy phục vụ RPC cần thiết, bởi giao thức NFS về cơ bản luôn tin tưởng dữ liệu nhận được từ mạng. Tường lửa cũng chặn <emphasis>việc làm giả IP</emphasis> để phòng ngừa việc một máy bên ngoài hành động như một máy bên trong, và truy cập tới các cổng tương ứng phải được giới hạn lại những máy chỉ dùng để truy cập các chia sẻ NFS."

msgid "<emphasis>BACK TO BASICS</emphasis> RPC"
msgstr "<emphasis>TRỞ VỀ CƠ BẢN</emphasis> RPC"

msgid "RPC (<emphasis>Remote Procedure Call</emphasis>) is a Unix standard for remote services. NFS is one such service."
msgstr "RPC (<emphasis>Remote Procedure Call(Thực thi Hàm Từ xa)</emphasis>) là một chuẩn Unix cho các dịch vụ chạy từ xa. NFS là một dịch vụ như vậy."

msgid "<primary>RPC</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>RPC</primary>"

msgid "<primary><emphasis>Remote Procedure Call</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>Thực thi Hàm Từ xa (Remote Procedure Call)</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "RPC services register to a directory known as the <emphasis>portmapper</emphasis>. A client wishing to perform an NFS query first addresses the <emphasis>portmapper</emphasis> (on port 111, either TCP or UDP), and asks for the NFS server; the reply usually mentions port 2049 (the default for NFS). Not all RPC services necessarily use a fixed port."
msgstr "Các dịch vụ RPC đăng ký với một danh bạ được biết đến như là <emphasis>danh bạ cổng (portmapper)</emphasis>. Một máy khách có ý muốn thực hiện một yêu cầu liên quan tới NFS trước tiên tìm đến <emphasis>danh bạ cổng (portmapper)</emphasis> (ở cổng 111, hoặc TCP hoặc UDP), và hỏi tìm máy phục vụ NFS; câu trả lời thường đề cập cổng 2049 (ngầm định cho NFS). Không phải tất cả các dịch vụ RPC cần sử dụng một cổng cố định."

msgid "Older versions of the protocol required other RPC services which used dynamically assigned ports. Fortunately, with NFS version 4, only port 2049 (for NFS) and 111 (for the portmapper) are needed and they are thus easy to firewall."
msgstr "Các phiên phản cũ hơn của giao thức buộc sự hiện diện của các dịch vụ RPC khác vốn dùng các cổng được gán linh động. May mắn thay, với phiên bản NFS 4, chỉ cổng 2049 (cho NFS) và 111 (cho danh bạ cổng) là cần thiết và tường lửa dễ dàng được cài đặt hơn."

msgid "<primary><command>portmapper</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>danh bạ cổng (portmapper)</command></primary>"

msgid "NFS Server"
msgstr "Máy phục vụ NFS"

msgid "The NFS server is part of the Linux kernel; in kernels provided by Debian it is built as a kernel module. If the NFS server is to be run automatically on boot, the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">nfs-kernel-server</emphasis> package should be installed; it contains the relevant start-up scripts."
msgstr "Máy phục vụ NFS là một phần của nhân(kernel) Linux; trong những nhân(kernel) được cung cấp bởi Debian nó được xây dựng như một mô-đun của nhân. Nếu máy phục vụ NFS được chạy tự động khi khởi động máy, gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">nfs-kernel-server</emphasis> nên được cài đặt; nó chứa các đoạn mã kịch bản khởi động có liên quan."

msgid "The NFS server configuration file, <filename>/etc/exports</filename>, lists the directories that are made available over the network (<emphasis>exported</emphasis>). For each NFS share, only the given list of machines is granted access. More fine-grained access control can be obtained with a few options. The syntax for this file is quite simple:"
msgstr "Tập tin cấu hình máy phục vụ NFS, <filename>/etc/exports</filename>, liệt kê những thư mục được tạo sẵn trên mạng (<emphasis>được xuất khẩu (exported)</emphasis>). Với mỗi chia sẻ NFS, chỉ có một danh sách các máy cho trước là được cung cấp truy cập. Kiểm soát truy cập chi tiết hơn có thể được đạt được với một vài lựa chọn. Cú pháp của tập tin này thì khá đơn giản:"

msgid "<primary><filename>exports</filename></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>exports</filename></primary>"

msgid "<primary><filename>/etc/exports</filename></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>/etc/exports</filename></primary>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"/directory/to/share machine1(option1,option2,...) machine2(...) ..."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"/đường_dẫn/tới/thư_mục_được_chia_sẻ máy-số_1(lựa_chọn_1,lựa_chọn_2,...) máy_số_2(...) ..."

msgid "Note that with NFSv4, all exported directories must be part of a single hierarchy and that the root directory of that hierarchy must be exported and identified with the option <literal>fsid=0</literal> or <literal>fsid=root</literal>."
msgstr "Ghi chú rằng với NFSv4, tất cả các thư mục được xuất khẩu phải là một phần của một cây duy nhất và thư mục gốc của cây đó phải được xuất ra và nhận dạng với lựa chọn <literal>fsid=0</literal> hoặc <literal>fsid=root</literal>."

msgid "Each machine can be identified either by its DNS name or its IP address. Whole sets of machines can also be specified using either a syntax such as <literal>*.falcot.com</literal> or an IP address range such as <literal>192.168.0.0/255.255.255.0</literal> or <literal>192.168.0.0/24</literal>."
msgstr "Mỗi máy có thể được nhận dạng bởi tên miền DNS của nó hoặc địa chỉ IP của nó. Các tập hợp đầy đủ các máy tính cũng có thể được chỉ định bằng cú pháp như <literal>*.falcot.com</literal> hoặc một vùng các địa chỉ IP như <literal>192.168.0.0/255.255.255.0</literal> hoặc <literal>192.168.0.0/24</literal>."

msgid "Directories are made available as read-only by default (or with the <literal>ro</literal> option). The <literal>rw</literal> option allows read-write access. NFS clients typically connect from a port restricted to root (in other words, below 1024); this restriction can be lifted by the <literal>insecure</literal> option (the <literal>secure</literal> option is implicit, but it can be made explicit if needed for clarity)."
msgstr "Các thư mục được tạo sẵn chỉ để đọc theo ngầm định (hoặc với lựa chọn <literal>ro</literal>). Lựa chọn <literal>rw</literal> cho phép truy cập đọc-viết. Những chương trình khách NFS thường kết nối từ một cổng giới hạn dành cho quản trị viên (root) (nói cách khác, dưới 1024); giới hạn này có thể được xóa bỏ bởi lựa chọn <literal>insecure</literal> (lựa chọn <literal>insecure</literal> luôn được ám chỉ, nhưng có thể được công khai nếu cần phải làm rõ)"

msgid "<primary>NFS</primary><secondary>options</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>NFS</primary><secondary>Các lựa chọn</secondary>"

msgid "By default, the server only answers an NFS query when the current disk operation is complete (<literal>sync</literal> option); this can be disabled with the <literal>async</literal> option. Asynchronous writes increase performance a bit, but they decrease reliability since there is a data loss risk in case of the server crashing between the acknowledgment of the write and the actual write on disk. Since the default value changed recently (as compared to the historical value of NFS), an explicit setting is recommended."
msgstr "Theo ngầm định, máy phục vụ chỉ trả lời một yêu cầu NFS khi một tác vụ hiện thời trên đĩa là hoàn tất (lựa chọn <literal>sync</literal>); điều này có thể được tắt bằng lựa chọn <literal>async</literal>. Các lần ghi không đồng bộ giúp tăng hiệu suất một chút, nhưng chúng giảm độ tin cậy bởi có nguy cơ mất dữ liệu trong trường hợp máy phục vụ gặp sự cố giữa lúc xác nhận việc ghi dữ liệu và hành động ghi dữ liệu thật sự lên đĩa cứng. Bởi giá trị ngầm định thay đổi trong thời gian gần đây (so với giá trị trước đây của NFS), một cài đặt công khai rõ ràng luôn được khuyến khích."

msgid "In order to not give root access to the filesystem to any NFS client, all queries appearing to come from a root user are considered by the server as coming from the <literal>nobody</literal> user. This behavior corresponds to the <literal>root_squash</literal> option, and is enabled by default. The <literal>no_root_squash</literal> option, which disables this behavior, is risky and should only be used in controlled environments. The <literal>anonuid=<replaceable>uid</replaceable></literal> and <literal>anongid=<replaceable>gid</replaceable></literal> options allow specifying another fake user to be used instead of UID/GID 65534 (which corresponds to user <literal>nobody</literal> and group <literal>nogroup</literal>)."
msgstr "Để tránh cho phép bất cứ chương trình khách NFS nào truy cập dưới quyền quản trị viên vào hệ thống tập tin, tất cả các truy cập trông như đến từ một tài khoản quyền quản trị viên được xem bởi máy phục vụ như là đến từ một tài khoản <literal>nobody</literal>. Hành vi này tương ứng với lựa chọn <literal>root_squash</literal>, và được kích hoạt theo ngầm định. Lựa chọn <literal>no_root_squash</literal>, vốn tắt hành vi này, là mạo hiểm và chỉ nên được sử dụng trong môi trường được kiểm soát. Lựa chọn <literal>anonuid=<replaceable>uid</replaceable></literal> và <literal>anongid=<replaceable>gid</replaceable></literal> cho phép việc chỉ định một tài khoản người dùng giả khác để được sử dụng thay cho UID/GID 65534 (vốn tương ứng với tài khoản <literal>nobody</literal> và nhóm <literal>nogroup</literal>)."

msgid "With NFSv4, you can add a <literal>sec</literal> option to indicate the security level that you want: <literal>sec=sys</literal> is the default with no special security features, <literal>sec=krb5</literal> enables authentication only, <literal>sec=krb5i</literal> adds integrity protection, and <literal>sec=krb5p</literal> is the most complete level which includes privacy protection (with data encryption). For this to work you need a working Kerberos setup (that service is not covered by this book)."
msgstr "Với NFSv4, bạn có thể thêm lựa chọn <literal>sec</literal> để chỉ định mức an ninh mà bạn muốn: <literal>sec=sys</literal> là mức ngầm định mà không có tính năng an ninh đặc biệt nào cả, <literal>sec=krb5</literal> chỉ kích hoạt xác thực, <literal>sec=krb5i</literal> thêm sự bảo vệ tính chặt chẽ, và <literal>sec=krb5p</literal> là mức hoàn thiện nhất vốn kèm cả sự bảo vệ tính riêng tư (với mã hóa dữ liệu). Để điều này hoạt động tốt bạn cần có một bản cài đặt Kerberos chạy tốt(dịch vụ đó không được giải thích bởi cuốn sách này)."

msgid "Other options are available; they are documented in the <citerefentry><refentrytitle>exports</refentrytitle> <manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry> manual page."
msgstr "Các lựa chọn khác cũng có sẵn; chúng được ghi lại trong trang <citerefentry><refentrytitle>exports</refentrytitle> <manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry> của tài liệu hướng dẫn."

msgid "<emphasis>CAUTION</emphasis> First installation"
msgstr "<emphasis>CẢNH BÁO</emphasis> Lần cài đặt đầu tiên"

msgid "The <filename>/etc/init.d/nfs-kernel-server</filename> boot script only starts the server if the <filename>/etc/exports</filename> lists one or more valid NFS shares. On initial configuration, once this file has been edited to contain valid entries, the NFS server must therefore be started with the following command:"
msgstr "Kịch bản khởi động <filename>/etc/init.d/nfs-kernel-server</filename> chỉ khởi động máy phục vụ nếu <filename>/etc/exports</filename> liệt kê một hoặc nhiều chia sẻ NFS hợp lệ. Với cấu hình ban đầu, một khi tập tin này được chỉnh sửa để chứa các chỉ mục hợp lệ, khi đó máy phục vụ NFS phải được khởi động với lệnh sau:"

msgid ""
"\n"
"<computeroutput># </computeroutput><userinput>service nfs-kernel-server start</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"<computeroutput># </computeroutput><userinput>service nfs-kernel-server start</userinput>"

msgid "NFS Client"
msgstr "Chương trình khách NFS"

msgid "<primary>client</primary><secondary>NFS</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>client</primary><secondary>NFS</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>NFS</primary><secondary>client</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>NFS</primary><secondary>chương trình khách</secondary>"

msgid "As with other filesystems, integrating an NFS share into the system hierarchy requires mounting. Since this filesystem has its peculiarities, a few adjustments were required in the syntaxes of the <command>mount</command> command and the <filename>/etc/fstab</filename> file."
msgstr "Giống như các hệ thống tập tin khác, việc tích hợp một chuẩn NFS vào cây hệ thống đòi hỏi phải có kết nối. Bởi hệ thống tập tin này khá khác biệt, một vài tùy chỉnh là cần thiết đối với cú pháp của lệnh <command>mount</command> và tập tin <filename>/etc/fstab</filename>."

msgid "Manually mounting with the <command>mount</command> command"
msgstr "Kết nối thủ công với lệnh <command>mount</command>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"          <computeroutput># </computeroutput><userinput>mount -t nfs4 -o rw,nosuid arrakis.internal.falcot.com:/shared /srv/shared</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"          <computeroutput># </computeroutput><userinput>mount -t nfs4 -o rw,nosuid arrakis.internal.falcot.com:/shared /srv/shared</userinput>"

msgid "NFS entry in the <filename>/etc/fstab</filename> file"
msgstr "Mục NFS trong tập tin <filename>/etc/fstab</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"arrakis.internal.falcot.com:/shared /srv/shared nfs4 rw,nosuid 0 0"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"arrakis.internal.falcot.com:/shared /srv/shared nfs4 rw,nosuid 0 0"

msgid "The entry described above mounts, at system startup, the <filename>/shared/</filename> NFS directory from the <literal>arrakis</literal> server into the local <filename>/srv/shared/</filename> directory. Read-write access is requested (hence the <literal>rw</literal> parameter). The <literal>nosuid</literal> option is a protection measure that wipes any <literal>setuid</literal> or <literal>setgid</literal> bit from programs stored on the share. If the NFS share is only meant to store documents, another recommended option is <literal>noexec</literal>, which prevents executing programs stored on the share. Note that on the server, the <filename>shared</filename> directory is below the NFSv4 root export (for example <filename>/export/shared</filename>), it is not a top-level directory."
msgstr "Mục được mô tả phía trên kết nối, khi hệ thống khởi động, thư mục NFS <filename>/shared/</filename> từ máy phục vụ <literal>arrakis</literal> vào thư mục nội bộ <filename>/srv/shared/</filename>. Truy cập đọc-ghi được yêu cầu (và vì thế có tham số <literal>rw</literal>). Lựa chọn <literal>nosuid</literal> là một biện pháp bảo vệ vốn dọn sạch các bit <literal>setuid</literal> or <literal>setgid</literal> khỏi những chương trình được lưu trong chia sẻ. Nếu chia sẻ NFS chỉ dành cho lưu trữ các tài liệu, một lựa chọn được đề xuất khác là <literal>noexec</literal>, vốn chặn các chương trình đang chạy lưu lên chia sẻ. Ghi chú rằng trên máy phục vụ, thư mục <filename>shared</filename> nằm dưới mục xuất khẩu gốc NFSv4 (ví dụ <filename>/export/shared</filename>), nó không phải là một thư mục gốc."

msgid "The <citerefentry><refentrytitle>nfs</refentrytitle> <manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry> manual page describes all the options in some detail."
msgstr "Trang hướng dẫn sử dụng <citerefentry><refentrytitle>nfs</refentrytitle> <manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry> mô tả các lựa chọn chi tiết hơn."

msgid "Setting Up Windows Shares with Samba"
msgstr "Cài đặt các chia sẻ Windows với Samba"

msgid "Samba is a suite of tools handling the SMB protocol (also known as “CIFS”) on Linux. This protocol is used by Windows for network shares and shared printers."
msgstr "Samba là một tập hợp các công cụ làm việc với giao thức SMB (cũng được biết đến như là “CIFS”) trên Linux. Giao thức này được sử dụng bởi Windows cho các chia sẻ qua mạng và chia sẻ máy in."

msgid "<primary>Windows share</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Chia sẻ Windows</primary>"

msgid "<primary>Samba</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Samba</primary>"

msgid "<primary>SMB</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>SMB</primary>"

msgid "<primary>CIFS</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>CIFS</primary>"

msgid "Samba can also act as an Windows domain controller. This is an outstanding tool for ensuring seamless integration of Linux servers and the office desktop machines still running Windows."
msgstr "Samba cũng có thể hoạt động như một trạm điều khiển miền máy tính (domain controller) của Windows. Nó là một công cụ tuyệt vời để đảm bảo tích hợp xuyên suốt với các máy phục vụ Linux và các máy tính bàn trong văn phòng vốn vẫn sử dụng Windows."

msgid "Samba Server"
msgstr "Máy phục vụ Samba"

msgid "The <emphasis role=\"pkg\">samba</emphasis> package contains the main two servers of Samba 4, <command>smbd</command> and <command>nmbd</command>."
msgstr "Gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">samba</emphasis> chứa hai máy phục vụ của Samba 4, <command>smbd</command> and <command>nmbd</command>."

msgid "<primary><command>smbd</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>smbd</command></primary>"

msgid "<primary><command>nmbd</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>nmbd</command></primary>"

msgid "<emphasis>DOCUMENTATION</emphasis> Going further"
msgstr "<emphasis>TÀI LIỆU HƯỚNG DẪN</emphasis> Đi sâu hơn"

msgid "The Samba server is extremely configurable and versatile, and can address a great many different use cases matching very different requirements and network architectures. This book only focuses on the use case where Samba is used as a standalone server, but it can also be a NT4 Domain Controller or a full Active Directory Domain Controller, or a simple member of an existing domain (which could be a managed by a Windows server)."
msgstr "Máy phục vụ Samba rất dễ cấu hình và đa dụng, và có thể hoạt động trong nhiều trường hợp với các yêu cầu và hạ tầng mạng ít có điểm chung. Cuốn sách này chỉ tập trung vào trường hợp Samba được sử dụng như một máy phục vụ đứng một mình, nhưng nó cũng có thể là một trạm điều khiển máy tính NT4(NT4 Domain Controller) hoặc một trạm điều khiển Active Directory(Active Directory Domain Controller), hoặc một thành viên đơn giản của một miền máy tính đã có (vốn có thể là một máy phục vụ Windows)."

msgid "<primary>domain controller</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>trạm điều khiển miền máy tính (domain controller)</primary>"

msgid "<primary>Windows domain</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Miền máy tính Windows(Windows domain)</primary>"

msgid "The <emphasis role=\"pkg\">samba-doc</emphasis> package contains a wealth of commented example files in <filename>/usr/share/doc/samba-doc/examples/</filename>."
msgstr "Gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">samba-doc</emphasis> chứa rất nhiều tập tin ví dụ được ghi chú trong <filename>/usr/share/doc/samba-doc/examples/</filename>."

msgid "<emphasis>TOOL</emphasis> Authenticating with a Windows Server"
msgstr "<emphasis>CÔNG CỤ</emphasis> Xác thực với một máy phục vụ Windows"

msgid "Winbind gives system administrators the option of using a Windows server as an authentication server. Winbind also integrates cleanly with PAM and NSS. This allows setting up Linux machines where all users of a Windows domain automatically get an account."
msgstr "Winbind cho các nhà quản trị hệ thống một lựa chọn sử dụng máy phục vụ Windows làm máy phục vụ việc xác thực. Winbind cũng tích hợp chặt với PAM và NSS. Điều này cho phép cài đặt các máy Linux mà tất cả những người sử dụng của một miền máy tính Windows tự động nhận được một tài khoản."

msgid "<primary>Winbind</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Winbind</primary>"

msgid "More information can be found in the <filename>/usr/share/doc/samba-doc/examples/pam_winbind/</filename> directory."
msgstr "Thông tin thêm có thể được tìm thấy ở thư mục <filename>/usr/share/doc/samba-doc/examples/pam_winbind/</filename>."

msgid "Configuring with <command>debconf</command>"
msgstr "Cấu hình với <command>debconf</command>"

msgid "The package sets up a minimal configuration during the initial installation but you should really run <command>dpkg-reconfigure samba-common</command> to adapt it:"
msgstr "Gói phần mềm này cài đặt một cấu hình đơn giản trong suốt quá trình cài đặt ban đầu nhưng bạn nên thực sự chạy lệnh <command>dpkg-reconfigure samba-common</command> để nó thích ứng:"

msgid "The first piece of required information is the name of the workgroup where the Samba server will belong (the answer is <literal>FALCOTNET</literal> in our case)."
msgstr "Mảnh thông tin bắt buộc đầu tiên là tên của nhóm làm việc(workgroup) mà máy phục vụ Samba thuộc về (câu trả lời là <literal>FALCOTNET</literal> trong trường hợp của chúng ta)."

msgid "The package also proposes identifying the WINS server from the information provided by the DHCP daemon. The Falcot Corp administrators rejected this option, since they intend to use the Samba server itself as the WINS server."
msgstr "Gói phần mềm này cũng đề xuất nhận dạng máy phục vụ WINS từ thông tin được cung cấp bởi dịch vụ nền DHCP. Các nhà quản trị hệ thống của Công ty Falcot từ chối lựa chọn này, bởi họ muốn dùng chính máy phục vụ Samba làm máy phục vụ WINS."

msgid "<primary>WINS</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>WINS</primary>"

msgid "Configuring Manually"
msgstr "Cấu hình thủ công"

msgid "Changes to <filename>smb.conf</filename>"
msgstr "Những thay đổi cho <filename>smb.conf</filename>"

msgid "The requirements at Falcot require other options to be modified in the <filename>/etc/samba/smb.conf</filename> configuration file. The following excerpts summarize the changes that were effected in the <literal>[global]</literal> section."
msgstr "Những yêu cầu tại Falcot bắt buộc các lựa chọn khác phải được thay đổi trong tập tin cấu hình <filename>/etc/samba/smb.conf</filename>. Đoạn mã sau tóm tắt các thay đổi trong phần <literal>[global]</literal>."

msgid ""
"\n"
"[global]\n"
"\n"
"## Browsing/Identification ###\n"
"\n"
"# Change this to the workgroup/NT-domain name your Samba server will part of\n"
"   workgroup = FALCOTNET\n"
"\n"
"# Windows Internet Name Serving Support Section:\n"
"# WINS Support - Tells the NMBD component of Samba to enable its WINS Server\n"
"   wins support = yes <co id=\"smb.conf.wins\"></co>\n"
"\n"
"[...]\n"
"\n"
"####### Authentication #######\n"
"\n"
"# Server role. Defines in which mode Samba will operate. Possible\n"
"# values are \"standalone server\", \"member server\", \"classic primary\n"
"# domain controller\", \"classic backup domain controller\", \"active\n"
"# directory domain controller\". \n"
"#\n"
"# Most people will want \"standalone sever\" or \"member server\".\n"
"# Running as \"active directory domain controller\" will require first\n"
"# running \"samba-tool domain provision\" to wipe databases and create a\n"
"# new domain.\n"
"   server role = standalone server\n"
"\n"
"# \"security = user\" is always a good idea. This will require a Unix account\n"
"# in this server for every user accessing the server.\n"
"   security = user <co id=\"smb.conf.security\"></co>\n"
"\n"
"[...]"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"[global]\n"
"\n"
"## Duyệt/Nhận dạng ###\n"
"\n"
"# Thay đổi dòng sau thành nhóm-làm-việc/miền-máy-tính-NT mà máy phục vụ Samba sẽ là một phần trong đó\n"
"   workgroup = FALCOTNET\n"
"\n"
"# Phần hỗ trợ Windows Internet Name Serving:\n"
"# WINS Support - Bảo thành phần NMBD của Samba để kích hoạt máy phục vụ WINS\n"
"   wins support = yes <co id=\"smb.conf.wins\"></co>\n"
"\n"
"[...]\n"
"\n"
"####### Xác thực #######\n"
"\n"
"# Vai trò máy phục vụ. Xác định chế độ mà Samba sẽ hoạt động. Các giá trị có khả thi\n"
"# là \"máy phục vụ đơn độc\", \"máy phục vụ thành viên\", \"trạm điều khiển miền máy tính chủ lực cổ điển \n"
"# (classic primary domain controller)\", \"trạm điều khiển miền máy tính dự phòng cổ điển\n"
"# (classic backup domain controller)\", \"trạm điều khiển miền máy tính active directory \n"
"# (active directory domain controller)\".\n"
"#\n"
"# Đa số người dùng sẽ muốn \"máy phục vụ đơn độc\" hoặc \"máy phục vụ thành viên\".\n"
"# Chạy như \"trạm điều khiển miền máy tính active directory\" sẽ buộc trước tiên\n"
"# chạy \"samba-tool domain provision\" để xóa sạch các cơ sở dữ liệu và tạo một miền máy tính\n"
"# mới.\n"
"   server role = standalone server\n"
"\n"
"# \"security = user\" luôn là một ý tốt. Điều này sẽ buộc phải có một tài khoản Unix\n"
"# trong máy phục vụ này cho mỗi người sử dụng truy cập máy phục vụ.\n"
"   security = user <co id=\"smb.conf.security\"></co>\n"
"\n"
"[...]"

msgid "Indicates that Samba should act as a Netbios name server (WINS) for the local network."
msgstr "Chỉ ra rằng Samba nên hoạt động như một máy phục vụ tên Netbios (Netbios name server) cho mạng nội bộ."

msgid "This is the default value for this parameter; however, since it is central to the Samba configuration, filling it explicitly is recommended. Each user must authenticate before accessing any share."
msgstr "Đây là giá trị ngầm định cho tham biến này; tuy nhiên, bởi nó là cốt lõi trong cấu hình Samba, điền giá trị vào một cách công khai được khuyến cáo. Mỗi người sử dụng phải xác thực trước khi truy cập một chia sẻ nào."

msgid "Adding Users"
msgstr "Thêm các người dùng"

msgid "Each Samba user needs an account on the server; the Unix accounts must be created first, then the user needs to be registered in Samba's database. The Unix step is done quite normally (using <command>adduser</command> for instance)."
msgstr "Mỗi một người sử dụng Samba cần một tài khoản trên máy phục vụ; các tài khoản Unix phải được tạo trước, sau đó mỗi người sử dụng cần phải được đăng ký vào cơ sở dữ liệu của Samba. Bước Unix được thực hiện như bình thường (ví dụ, sử dụng lệnh <command>adduser</command>)."

msgid "Adding an existing user to the Samba database is a matter of running the <command>smbpasswd -a <replaceable>user</replaceable></command> command; this command asks for the password interactively."
msgstr "Thêm một người dùng đã tồn tại vào cơ sở dữ liệu Samba chỉ cần chạy lệnh <command>smbpasswd -a <replaceable>user</replaceable></command>; lệnh này hỏi mật mã theo cách tương tác trực tiếp."

msgid "A user can be deleted with the <command>smbpasswd -x <replaceable>user</replaceable></command> command. A Samba account can also be temporarily disabled (with <command>smbpasswd -d <replaceable>user</replaceable></command>) and re-enabled later (with <command>smbpasswd -e <replaceable>user</replaceable></command>)."
msgstr "Một người sử dụng có thể bị xóa với lệnh <command>smbpasswd -x <replaceable>user</replaceable></command>. Một tài khoản Samba có thể bị tắt đi tạm thời (với lệnh <command>smbpasswd -d <replaceable>user</replaceable></command>) và được kích hoạt lại sau đó (với lệnh <command>smbpasswd -e <replaceable>user</replaceable></command>)."

msgid "Samba Client"
msgstr "Chương trình khách Samba"

msgid "The client features in Samba allow a Linux machine to access Windows shares and shared printers. The required programs are available in the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">cifs-utils</emphasis> and <emphasis role=\"pkg\">smbclient</emphasis> packages."
msgstr "Các tính năng của chương trình khách trong Samba cho phép một máy tính Linux truy cập các chia sẻ và các máy in được chia sẻ của Windows. Các chương trình bắt buộc đã có sẵn trong các gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">cifs-utils</emphasis> và <emphasis role=\"pkg\">smbclient</emphasis>."

msgid "<primary><emphasis>smbclient</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>smbclient</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "<primary><emphasis>cifs-utils</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>cifs-utils</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "The <command>smbclient</command> Program"
msgstr "Chương trình <command>smbclient</command> "

msgid "The <command>smbclient</command> program queries SMB servers. It accepts a <literal>-U <replaceable>user</replaceable></literal> option, for connecting to the server under a specific identity. <command>smbclient //<replaceable>server</replaceable>/<replaceable>share</replaceable></command> accesses the share in an interactive way similar to the command-line FTP client. <command>smbclient -L <replaceable>server</replaceable></command> lists all available (and visible) shares on a server."
msgstr "Chương trình <command>smbclient</command> truy xuất các máy phục vụ SMB. Nó chấp nhận lựa chọn <literal>-U <replaceable>user</replaceable></literal>, để kết nối tới máy phục vụ dưới một danh tính cụ thể nào đó. Lệnh <command>smbclient //<replaceable>server</replaceable>/<replaceable>share</replaceable></command> truy cập chia sẻ đó theo một cách có tương tác tương tự như chương trình khách FTP trên dòng lệnh. Lệnh <command>smbclient -L <replaceable>server</replaceable></command> liệt kê tất cả các chia sẻ có sẵn (và nhìn thấy được) trên một máy phục vụ."

msgid "Mounting Windows Shares"
msgstr "Kết nối các chia sẻ Windows"

msgid "The <command>mount</command> command allows mounting a Windows share into the Linux filesystem hierarchy (with the help of <command>mount.cifs</command> provided by <emphasis role=\"pkg\">cifs-utils</emphasis>)."
msgstr "Lệnh <command>mount</command> cho phép kết nối một chia sẻ Windows vào một cây hệ thống tập tin Linux (với sự giúp đỡ của <command>mount.cifs</command> được cung cấp bởi <emphasis role=\"pkg\">cifs-utils</emphasis>)."

msgid "<primary><command>mount.cifs</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>mount.cifs</command></primary>"

msgid "<primary>Windows share, mounting</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Chia sẻ Windows, kết nối</primary>"

msgid "Mounting a Windows share"
msgstr "Kết nối một chia sẻ Windows"

msgid ""
"\n"
"mount -t cifs //arrakis/shared /shared \\\n"
"      -o credentials=/etc/smb-credentials"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"mount -t cifs //arrakis/shared /shared \\\n"
"      -o credentials=/etc/smb-credentials"

msgid "The <filename>/etc/smb-credentials</filename> file (which must not be readable by users) has the following format:"
msgstr "Tập tin <filename>/etc/smb-credentials</filename> (vốn phải không đọc được bởi người sử dụng) có định dạng sau:"

msgid ""
"\n"
"username = <replaceable>user</replaceable>\n"
"password = <replaceable>password</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"username = <replaceable>user</replaceable>\n"
"password = <replaceable>password</replaceable>"

msgid "Other options can be specified on the command-line; their full list is available in the <citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle> <manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry> manual page. Two options in particular can be interesting: <literal>uid</literal> and <literal>gid</literal> allow forcing the owner and group of files available on the mount, so as not to restrict access to root."
msgstr "Các lựa chọn khác có thể được chỉ định trên dòng lệnh; danh sách đầy đủ của chúng có sẵn trong trang hướng dẫn sử dụng <citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle> <manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry>. Hai lựa chọn cụ thể có thể thú vị: <literal>uid</literal> và <literal>gid</literal> cho phép ép buộc người sở hữu và danh sách các tập tin sẽ được hiện ra trên kết nối, để khỏi phải giới hạn truy cập chỉ cho tài khoản quản trị."

msgid "A mount of a Windows share can also be configured in <filename>/etc/fstab</filename>:"
msgstr "Một chia sẻ Windows cũng có thể được cấu hình trong <filename>/etc/fstab</filename>:"

msgid ""
"\n"
"//<replaceable>server</replaceable>/shared /shared cifs credentials=/etc/smb-credentials"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"//<replaceable>server</replaceable>/shared /shared cifs credentials=/etc/smb-credentials"

msgid "Unmounting a SMB/CIFS share is done with the standard <command>umount</command> command."
msgstr "Bỏ kết nối SMB/CIFS được thực hiện với lệnh <command>umount</command>."

msgid "Printing on a Shared Printer"
msgstr "In ấn trên một máy in được chia sẻ"

msgid "CUPS is an elegant solution for printing from a Linux workstation to a printer shared by a Windows machine. When the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">smbclient</emphasis> is installed, CUPS allows installing Windows shared printers automatically."
msgstr "CUPS là một giải pháp tiện lợi cho in ấn từ một máy trạm Linux sang một máy in được chia sẻ bởi một máy Windows. Khi <emphasis role=\"pkg\">smbclient</emphasis> được cài đặt, CUPS cho phép cài đặt các máy in được chia sẻ bởi Windows một cách tự động."

msgid "<primary>printing</primary><secondary>network</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>printing</primary><secondary>network</secondary>"

msgid "Here are the required steps:"
msgstr "Đây là các bước bắt buộc:"

msgid "Enter the CUPS configuration interface: <literal>http://localhost:631/admin</literal>"
msgstr "Nhập vào địa chỉ của giao diện cấu hình CUPS: <literal>http://localhost:631/admin</literal>"

msgid "Click on “Add Printer”."
msgstr "Nhấn chuộc vào “Thêm Máy In (Add Printer)”."

msgid "Choose the printer device, pick “Windows Printer via SAMBA”."
msgstr "Chọn thiết bị in, chọn “Máy in Windows thông qua SAMBA“."

msgid "Enter the connection URI for the network printer. It should look like the following:"
msgstr "Nhập đường dẫn URI cho kết nối đến máy in mạng. Nó giống như sau:"

msgid "<literal>smb://<replaceable>user</replaceable>:<replaceable>password</replaceable>@<replaceable>server</replaceable>/<replaceable>printer</replaceable></literal>."
msgstr "<literal>smb://<replaceable>user</replaceable>:<replaceable>password</replaceable>@<replaceable>server</replaceable>/<replaceable>printer</replaceable></literal>."

msgid "Enter the name that will uniquely identify this printer. Then enter the description and location of the printer. Those are the strings that will be shown to end users to help them identify the printers."
msgstr "Nhập tên vốn sẽ nhận diện được ngay máy in này. Sau đó nhập mô tả và địa điểm của máy in. Đó là những chuỗi ký tự sẽ được xuất ra cho những người dùng cuối để giúp họ nhận ra các máy in."

msgid "Indicate the manufacturer/model of the printer, or directly provide a working printer description file (PPD)."
msgstr "Báo nhà sản xuất/mô-đen của máy in hoặc trực tiếp cung cấp một tập tin mô tả máy in đang chạy tốt (Printer Description file - PPD)."

msgid "Voilà, the printer is operational!"
msgstr "Voilà, máy in đã hoạt động!"

msgid "HTTP/FTP Proxy"
msgstr "Trạm chuyển hướng HTTP/FTP"

msgid "An HTTP/FTP proxy acts as an intermediary for HTTP and/or FTP connections. Its role is twofold:"
msgstr "Một trạm chuyển hướng HTTP/FTP hoạt động như một bên trung gian cho các kết nối HTTP và/hoặc FTP. Vai trò của nó có hai mặt:"

msgid "Caching: recently downloaded documents are copied locally, which avoids multiple downloads."
msgstr "Bộ nhớ tạm thời: các tài liệu được tải về gần đây được sao chép nội bộ, vốn tránh được sự trùng lặp trong việc tải xuống."

msgid "Filtering server: if use of the proxy is mandated (and outgoing connections are blocked unless they go through the proxy), then the proxy can determine whether or not the request is to be granted."
msgstr "Máy phục vụ cho việc lọc: nếu bắt buộc phải dùng trạm chuyển hướng (và các kết nối đi ra bên ngoài bị chặn trừ khi chúng đi thông qua trạm chuyển hướng), trạm chuyển hướng có thể quyết định một yêu cầu có được chấp thuận hay không."

msgid "<primary>HTTP/FTP proxy</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>HTTP/FTP proxy</primary>"

msgid "<primary>proxy cache</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>bộ nhớ tạm thời của trạm chuyển hướng</primary>"

msgid "Falcot Corp selected Squid as their proxy server."
msgstr "Công ty Falcot đã lựa chọn Squid làm máy phục vụ trạm chuyển hướng của họ."

msgid "<primary>Squid</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Squid</primary>"

msgid "Installing"
msgstr "Cài đặt"

msgid "The <emphasis role=\"pkg\">squid3</emphasis> Debian package only contains the modular (caching) proxy. Turning it into a filtering server requires installing the additional <emphasis role=\"pkg\">squidguard</emphasis> package. In addition, <emphasis role=\"pkg\">squid-cgi</emphasis> provides a querying and administration interface for a Squid proxy."
msgstr "Gói phần mềm Debian <emphasis role=\"pkg\">squid3</emphasis> chỉ chứa trạm chuyển hướng có cấu hình mô-đun (có bộ nhớ tạm). Biến nó thành một máy phục vụ lọc buộc phải cài đặt thêm gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">squidguard</emphasis>. Ngoài ra, <emphasis role=\"pkg\">squid-cgi</emphasis> cung cấp một giao diện truy xuất và quản trị cho một trạm trung chuyển Squid."

msgid "Prior to installing, care should be taken to check that the system can identify its own complete name: the <command>hostname -f</command> must return a fully-qualified name (including a domain). If it does not, then the <filename>/etc/hosts</filename> file should be edited to contain the full name of the system (for instance, <literal>arrakis.falcot.com</literal>). The official computer name should be validated with the network administrator in order to avoid potential name conflicts."
msgstr "Trước khi cài đặt, phải cẩn thận kiểm tra xem hệ thống có nhận diện được tên đầy đủ của nó không: lệnh <command>hostname -f</command> phải trả về một tên đầy đủ (bao gồm cả tên miền). Nếu không, tập tin <filename>/etc/hosts</filename> phải được sửa đổi để chứa tên đầy đủ của hệ thống (ví dụ, <literal>arrakis.falcot.com</literal>). Tên chính thức của máy tính nên được kiểm tra với nhà quản trị mạng để tránh xung đột tên có thể có."

msgid "Configuring a Cache"
msgstr "Cấu hình một Bộ nhớ tạm thời"

msgid "Enabling the caching server feature is a simple matter of editing the <filename>/etc/squid3/squid.conf</filename> configuration file and allowing machines from the local network to run queries through the proxy. The following example shows the modifications made by the Falcot Corp administrators:"
msgstr "Kích hoạt tính năng bộ nhớ tạm thời chỉ đơn giản là chỉnh sửa tập tin cấu hình <filename>/etc/squid3/squid.conf</filename> và cho phép các máy tính từ miền nội bộ chạy các truy xuất thông qua trạm chuyển hướng. Ví dụ sau cho thấy những thay đổi được tạo ra bởi các nhà quản trị hệ thống của Công ty Falcot:"

msgid "The <filename>/etc/squid3/squid.conf</filename> file (excerpts)"
msgstr "Tập tin <filename>/etc/squid3/squid.conf</filename> (những trích đoạn)"

msgid ""
"\n"
"# INSERT YOUR OWN RULE(S) HERE TO ALLOW ACCESS FROM YOUR CLIENTS\n"
"\n"
"# Example rule allowing access from your local networks. Adapt\n"
"# to list your (internal) IP networks from where browsing should\n"
"# be allowed\n"
"acl our_networks src 192.168.1.0/24 192.168.2.0/24\n"
"http_access allow our_networks\n"
"http_access allow localhost\n"
"# And finally deny all other access to this proxy\n"
"http_access deny all"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"# CHÈN NHỮNG QUY TẮC CỦA BẠN VÀO ĐÂY ĐỂ CHO PHÉP CÁC CHƯƠNG TRÌNH KHÁCH TRUY CẬP\n"
"\n"
"# Quy tắc ví dụ cho phép truy cập từ những mạng nội bộ. Chỉnh sửa nó\n"
