msgid "The <command>ldap</command> module is usually inserted before others, and it will therefore be queried first. The notable exception is the <literal>hosts</literal> service since contacting the LDAP server requires consulting DNS first (to resolve <literal>ldap.falcot.com</literal>). Without this exception, a hostname query would try to ask the LDAP server; this would trigger a name resolution for the LDAP server, and so on in an infinite loop."
msgstr "Mô-đun <command>ldap</command> thường được chèn trước những mô-đun khác, và vì thế nó sẽ được hỏi trước. Ngoại lệ đáng chú ý là dịch vụ <literal>hosts</literal> bởi liên lạc với máy phục vụ LDAP cần phải hỏi DNS trước (để giải mã tên <literal>ldap.falcot.com</literal>). Không có ngoại lệ, một truy xuất tên máy tính sẽ cố gắng hỏi máy phục vụ LDAP; điều này sẽ kích hoạt giải mã tên miền cho máy phục vụ LDAP, và vâng vâng trong một vòng lặp vô hạn."

msgid "If the LDAP server should be considered authoritative (and the local files used by the <command>files</command> module disregarded), services can be configured with the following syntax:"
msgstr "Nếu máy phục vụ LDAP nên được xem như nguồn thông tin chính xác (và các tập tin nội bộ được sử dụng bởi mô-đun <command>files</command> bị bỏ qua), các dịch vụ có thể được cấu hình với cú pháp sau:"

msgid "<literal><replaceable>service</replaceable>: ldap [NOTFOUND=return] files</literal>."
msgstr "<literal><replaceable>service</replaceable>: ldap [NOTFOUND=return] files</literal>."

msgid "If the requested entry does not exist in the LDAP database, the query will return a “not existing” reply even if the resource does exist in one of the local files; these local files will only be used when the LDAP service is down."
msgstr "Nếu mục được yêu cầu không tồn tại trong cơ sở dữ liệu LDAP, truy xuất sẽ trả về một câu trả lời “không tồn tại“ thậm chí nếu tài nguyên đó có tồn tại trong một trong các tập tin nội bộ; các tập tin nội bộ này sẽ chỉ được sử dụng nếu dịch vụ LDAP bị sập."

msgid "Configuring PAM"
msgstr "Cấu hình PAM"

msgid "This section describes a PAM configuration (see sidebar <xref linkend=\"sidebar.intro-pam\" />) that will allow applications to perform the required authentications against the LDAP database."
msgstr "Phần này mô tả một cấu hình PAM (xem ở thanh bên cạnh <xref linkend=\"sidebar.intro-pam\" />) vốn sẽ cho phép các ứng dung thực hiện các xác thực cần thiết dựa trên cơ sở dữ liệu LDAP."

msgid "<emphasis>CAUTION</emphasis> Broken authentication"
msgstr "<emphasis>CẢNH BÁO</emphasis> Xác thực sai"

msgid "Changing the standard PAM configuration used by various programs is a sensitive operation. A mistake can lead to broken authentication, which could prevent logging in. Keeping a root shell open is therefore a good precaution. If configuration errors occur, they can be then fixed and the services restarted with minimal effort."
msgstr "Thay đổi cấu hình PAM chuẩn vốn được sử dụng bởi nhiều chương trình là một hành động nhạy cảm. Một lỗi có thể dẫn đến xác thực sai, và chặn việc đăng nhập. Giữ một cửa sổ dòng lệnh với quyền quản trị vì thế là một cách phòng chống tốt. Nếu các lỗi cấu hình xảy ra, chúng có thể được sửa và các dịch vụ khởi động lại mà ít tốn công sức."

msgid "The LDAP module for PAM is provided by the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libpam-ldap</emphasis> package. Installing this package asks a few questions very similar to those in <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libnss-ldap</emphasis>; some configuration parameters (such as the URI for the LDAP server) are even actually shared with the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libnss-ldap</emphasis> package. Answers are summarized in <xref linkend=\"tab-libpam-ldap\" xrefstyle=\"select: label nopage\" />."
msgstr "Mô-đun LDAP cho PAM được cung cấp bởi gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libpam-ldap</emphasis>. Cài đặt gói phần mềm này hỏi một vài câu hỏi tương tự những câu hỏi ở <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libnss-ldap</emphasis>; một vài tham biến cấu hình (như là Đường dẫn Chuẩn đến Tài nguyên (URI) cho máy phục vụ LDAP) thậm chí thực ra được chia sẻ với gói <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libnss-ldap</emphasis>. Các câu trả lời được tóm tắt ở <xref linkend=\"tab-libpam-ldap\" xrefstyle=\"select: label nopage\" />."

msgid "<primary><emphasis>libpam-ldap</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>libpam-ldap</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "Configuration of <emphasis>libpam-ldap</emphasis>"
msgstr "Cấu hình của <emphasis>libpam-ldap</emphasis>"

msgid "Allow LDAP admin account to behave like local root?"
msgstr "Cho phép tài khoản quản trị LDAP hành động như một quản trị viên của máy nội bộ"

msgid "Yes. This allows using the usual <command>passwd</command> command for changing passwords stored in the LDAP database."
msgstr "Đồng ý. Điều này cho phép sử dụng lệnh thông thường <command>passwd</command> để thay đổi mật mã lưu trong cơ sở dữ liệu LDAP"

msgid "Does the LDAP database require logging in?"
msgstr "LDAP có bắt buộc đăng nhập?"

msgid "the LDAP database administrative password"
msgstr "mật mã quản trị cơ sở dữ liệu LDAP"

msgid "Local encryption algorithm to use for passwords"
msgstr "Thuật toán mã hóa nội bộ để sử dụng cho các mật mã"

msgid "crypt"
msgstr "crypt"

msgid "Installing <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libpam-ldap</emphasis> automatically adapts the default PAM configuration defined in the <filename>/etc/pam.d/common-auth</filename>, <filename>/etc/pam.d/common-password</filename> and <filename>/etc/pam.d/common-account</filename> files. This mechanism uses the dedicated <command>pam-auth-update</command> tool (provided by the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libpam-runtime</emphasis> package). This tool can also be run by the administrator should they wish to enable or disable PAM modules."
msgstr "Việc cài đặt <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libpam-ldap</emphasis> sẽ tự động thay đổi cấu hình định nghĩa trong các tập tin <filename>/etc/pam.d/common-auth</filename>, <filename>/etc/pam.d/common-password</filename> và <filename>/etc/pam.d/common-account</filename>. Cơ chế này sử dụng công cụ chuyên dụng <command>pam-auth-update</command> (cung cấp bởi gói phần mềm <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libpam-runtime</emphasis>). Công cụ này cũng có thể được chạy bởi quản trị viên nếu họ muốn kích hoạt hay bỏ kích hoạt các mô-đun PAM."

